{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "NUM"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Numbers \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Fourth Book of Musa, Commonly Called Numbers \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Numbers \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Num \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Fourth Book of Musa, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt3", "content": ["Commonly Called \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Numbers \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 1:1"}, "The LORD", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " spoke to Musa in the wilderness of Sinai, in the Tent of Meeting, on the first day of the second month, in the second\nyear after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 1:2"}, "\u201cTake a census of all the congregation of the children of Israel, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according\nto the number of the names, every male, one by one, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 1:3"}, "from twenty years old and upward, all who are able to go out to war in Israel. You and Harun shall count them by their\ndivisions. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 1:4"}, "With you there shall be a man of every tribe, each one head of his fathers\u2019 house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 1:5"}, "These are the names of the men who shall stand with you: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Of Reuben: Elizur the son of Shedeur. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 1:6"}, "Of Simeon: Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 1:7"}, "Of Judah: Nahshon the son of Amminadab. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 1:8"}, "Of Issachar: Nethanel the son of Zuar. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 1:9"}, "Of Zebulun: Eliab the son of Helon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 1:10"}, "Of the children of Yusuf: of Ephraim: Elishama the son of Ammihud; of Manasseh: Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 1:11"}, "Of Benjamin: Abidan the son of Gideoni. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 1:12"}, "Of Dan: Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 1:13"}, "Of Asher: Pagiel the son of Ochran. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 1:14"}, "Of Gad: Eliasaph the son of Deuel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 1:15"}, "Of Naphtali: Ahira the son of Enan.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 1:16"}, "These are those who were called of the congregation, the princes", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, chiefs, or, leaders"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of the tribes of their fathers; they were the heads of the thousands of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 1:17"}, "Musa and Harun took these men who are mentioned by name. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 1:18"}, "They assembled all the congregation together on the first day of the second month; and they declared their ancestry by\ntheir families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, one by one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 1:19"}, "As the LORD commanded Musa, so he counted them in the wilderness of Sinai.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 1:20"}, "The children of Reuben, Israel\u2019s firstborn, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to\nthe number of the names, one by one, every male from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 1:21"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Reuben, were forty-six thousand and five hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 1:22"}, "Of the children of Simeon, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, those who were counted of it,\naccording to the number of the names, one by one, every male from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to\nwar: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 1:23"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Simeon, were fifty-nine thousand and three hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 1:24"}, "Of the children of Gad, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of the\nnames, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 1:25"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Gad, were forty-five thousand and six hundred and fifty.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 1:26"}, "Of the children of Judah, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of the\nnames, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 1:27"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Judah, were seventy-four thousand and six hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 1:28"}, "Of the children of Issachar, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of\nthe names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 1:29"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Issachar, were fifty-four thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 1:30"}, "Of the children of Zebulun, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of\nthe names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 1:31"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Zebulun, were fifty-seven thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 1:32"}, "Of the children of Yusuf: of the children of Ephraim, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses,\naccording to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 1:33"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Ephraim, were forty thousand and five hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 1:34"}, "Of the children of Manasseh, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of\nthe names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 1:35"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Manasseh, were thirty-two thousand and two hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 1:36"}, "Of the children of Benjamin, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of\nthe names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 1:37"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Benjamin, were thirty-five thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 1:38"}, "Of the children of Dan, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of the\nnames, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 1:39"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Dan, were sixty-two thousand and seven hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 1:40"}, "Of the children of Asher, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of the\nnames, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 1:41"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Asher, were forty-one thousand and five hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 1:42"}, "Of the children of Naphtali, their generations, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, according to the number of\nthe names, from twenty years old and upward, all who were able to go out to war:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 1:43"}, "those who were counted of them, of the tribe of Naphtali, were fifty-three thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 1:44"}, "These are those who were counted, whom Musa and Harun counted, and the twelve men who were princes of Israel, each one\nfor his fathers\u2019 house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 1:45"}, "So all those who were counted of the children of Israel by their fathers\u2019 houses, from twenty years old and upward, all\nwho were able to go out to war in Israel\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 1:46"}, "all those who were counted were six hundred and three thousand and five hundred and fifty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 1:47"}, "But the Levites after the tribe of their fathers were not counted amongst them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 1:48"}, "For the LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 1:49"}, "\u201cOnly the tribe of Levi you shall not count, neither shall you take a census of them amongst the children of Israel;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 1:50"}, "but appoint the Levites over the Tabernacle of the Testimony, and over all its furnishings, and over all that belongs to\nit. They shall carry the tabernacle and all its furnishings; and they shall take care of it, and shall encamp around it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "NUM 1:51"}, "When the tabernacle is to move, the Levites shall take it down; and when the tabernacle is to be set up, the Levites\nshall set it up. The stranger who comes near shall be put to death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "NUM 1:52"}, "The children of Israel shall pitch their tents, every man by his own camp, and every man by his own standard, according\nto their divisions. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "NUM 1:53"}, "But the Levites shall encamp around the Tabernacle of the Testimony, that there may be no wrath on the congregation of\nthe children of Israel. The Levites shall be responsible for the Tabernacle of the Testimony.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "NUM 1:54"}, "Thus the children of Israel did. According to all that the LORD commanded Musa, so they did.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 2:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and to Harun, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 2:2"}, "\u201cThe children of Israel shall encamp every man by his own standard, with the banners of their fathers\u2019 houses. They shall\nencamp around the Tent of Meeting at a distance from it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 2:3"}, "Those who encamp on the east side towards the sunrise shall be of the standard of the camp of Judah, according to their\ndivisions. The prince of the children of Judah shall be Nahshon the son of Amminadab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 2:4"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were seventy-four thousand and six hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 2:5"}, "Those who encamp next to him shall be the tribe of Issachar. The prince of the children of Issachar shall be Nethanel the\nson of Zuar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 2:6"}, "His division, and those who were counted of it, were fifty-four thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 2:7"}, "The tribe of Zebulun: the prince of the children of Zebulun shall be Eliab the son of Helon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 2:8"}, "His division, and those who were counted of it, were fifty-seven thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 2:9"}, "All who were counted of the camp of Judah were one hundred and eighty-six thousand and four hundred, according to their\ndivisions. They shall set out first. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 2:10"}, "\u201cOn the south side shall be the standard of the camp of Reuben according to their divisions. The prince of the children\nof Reuben shall be Elizur the son of Shedeur. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 2:11"}, "His division, and those who were counted of it, were forty-six thousand and five hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 2:12"}, "\u201cThose who encamp next to him shall be the tribe of Simeon. The prince of the children of Simeon shall be Shelumiel the\nson of Zurishaddai. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 2:13"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were fifty-nine thousand and three hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 2:14"}, "\u201cThe tribe of Gad: the prince of the children of Gad shall be Eliasaph the son of Reuel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 2:15"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were forty-five thousand and six hundred and fifty.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 2:16"}, "\u201cAll who were counted of the camp of Reuben were one hundred and fifty-one thousand and four hundred and fifty, according\nto their armies. They shall set out second. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 2:17"}, "\u201cThen the Tent of Meeting shall set out, with the camp of the Levites in the middle of the camps. As they encamp, so\nshall they set out, every man in his place, by their standards. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 2:18"}, "\u201cOn the west side shall be the standard of the camp of Ephraim according to their divisions. The prince of the children\nof Ephraim shall be Elishama the son of Ammihud. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 2:19"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were forty thousand and five hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 2:20"}, "\u201cNext to him shall be the tribe of Manasseh. The prince of the children of Manasseh shall be Gamaliel the son of\nPedahzur. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 2:21"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were thirty-two thousand and two hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 2:22"}, "\u201cThe tribe of Benjamin: the prince of the children of Benjamin shall be Abidan the son of Gideoni.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 2:23"}, "His army, and those who were counted of them, were thirty-five thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 2:24"}, "\u201cAll who were counted of the camp of Ephraim were one hundred and eight thousand and one hundred, according to their\ndivisions. They shall set out third. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 2:25"}, "\u201cOn the north side shall be the standard of the camp of Dan according to their divisions. The prince of the children of\nDan shall be Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 2:26"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were sixty-two thousand and seven hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 2:27"}, "\u201cThose who encamp next to him shall be the tribe of Asher. The prince of the children of Asher shall be Pagiel the son of\nOchran. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 2:28"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were forty-one thousand and five hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 2:29"}, "\u201cThe tribe of Naphtali: the prince of the children of Naphtali shall be Ahira the son of Enan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 2:30"}, "His division, and those who were counted of them, were fifty-three thousand and four hundred.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 2:31"}, "\u201cAll who were counted of the camp of Dan were one hundred and fifty-seven thousand and six hundred. They shall set out\nlast by their standards.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 2:32"}, "These are those who were counted of the children of Israel by their fathers\u2019 houses. All who were counted of the camps\naccording to their armies were six hundred and three thousand and five hundred and fifty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 2:33"}, "But the Levites were not counted amongst the children of Israel, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 2:34"}, "Thus the children of Israel did. According to all that the LORD commanded Musa, so they encamped by their standards, and\nso they set out, everyone by their families, according to their fathers\u2019 houses.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 3:1"}, "Now this is the history of the generations of Harun and Musa in the day that the LORD spoke with Musa in Mount Sinai.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 3:2"}, "These are the names of the sons of Harun: Nadab the firstborn, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 3:3"}, "These are the names of the sons of Harun, the priests who were anointed, whom he consecrated to minister in the priest\u2019s\noffice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 3:4"}, "Nadab and Abihu died before the LORD when they offered strange fire before the LORD in the wilderness of Sinai, and they\nhad no children. Eleazar and Ithamar ministered in the priest\u2019s office in the presence of Harun their father.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 3:5"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 3:6"}, "\u201cBring the tribe of Levi near, and set them before Harun the priest, that they may minister to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 3:7"}, "They shall keep his requirements, and the requirements of the whole congregation before the Tent of Meeting, to do the\nservice of the tabernacle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 3:8"}, "They shall keep all the furnishings of the Tent of Meeting, and the obligations of the children of Israel, to do the\nservice of the tabernacle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 3:9"}, "You shall give the Levites to Harun and to his sons. They are wholly given to him on the behalf of the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 3:10"}, "You shall appoint Harun and his sons, and they shall keep their priesthood, but the stranger who comes near shall be put\nto death.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 3:11"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 3:12"}, "\u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often\nused as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I have taken the Levites from amongst the children of Israel instead of all the firstborn who open\nthe womb amongst the children of Israel; and the Levites shall be mine,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 3:13"}, "for all the firstborn are mine. On the day that I struck down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I made holy to me\nall the firstborn in Israel, both man and animal. They shall be mine. I am the LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 3:14"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa in the wilderness of Sinai, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 3:15"}, "\u201cCount the children of Levi by their fathers\u2019 houses, by their families. You shall count every male from a month old and\nupward.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 3:16"}, "Musa counted them according to the LORD\u2019s word, as he was commanded.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 3:17"}, "These were the sons of Levi by their names: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 3:18"}, "These are the names of the sons of Gershon by their families: Libni and Shimei.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 3:19"}, "The sons of Kohath by their families: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 3:20"}, "The sons of Merari by their families: Mahli and Mushi. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["These are the families of the Levites according to their fathers\u2019 houses.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 3:21"}, "Of Gershon was the family of the Libnites, and the family of the Shimeites. These are the families of the Gershonites.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 3:22"}, "Those who were counted of them, according to the number of all the males from a month old and upward, even those who were\ncounted of them were seven thousand and five hundred. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 3:23"}, "The families of the Gershonites shall encamp behind the tabernacle westward.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 3:24"}, "Eliasaph the son of Lael shall be the prince of the fathers\u2019 house of the Gershonites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 3:25"}, "The duty of the sons of Gershon in the Tent of Meeting shall be the tabernacle, the tent, its covering, the screen for\nthe door of the Tent of Meeting, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 3:26"}, "the hangings of the court, the screen for the door of the court which is by the tabernacle and around the altar, and its\ncords for all of its service. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 3:27"}, "Of Kohath was the family of the Amramites, the family of the Izharites, the family of the Hebronites, and the family of\nthe Uzzielites. These are the families of the Kohathites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 3:28"}, "According to the number of all the males from a month old and upward, there were eight thousand and six hundred keeping\nthe requirements of the sanctuary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 3:29"}, "The families of the sons of Kohath shall encamp on the south side of the tabernacle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 3:30"}, "The prince of the fathers\u2019 house of the families of the Kohathites shall be Elizaphan the son of Uzziel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 3:31"}, "Their duty shall be the ark, the table, the lamp stand, the altars, the vessels of the sanctuary with which they\nminister, the screen, and all its service. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 3:32"}, "Eleazar the son of Harun the priest shall be prince of the princes of the Levites, with the oversight of those who keep\nthe requirements of the sanctuary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 3:33"}, "Of Merari was the family of the Mahlites and the family of the Mushites. These are the families of Merari.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 3:34"}, "Those who were counted of them, according to the number of all the males from a month old and upward, were six thousand\nand two hundred.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["+ 22,000 is the sum rounded to 2 significant digits. The sum of the Gershonites, Kohathites,\nand Merarites given above is 22,300, but the traditional Hebrew text has the number rounded to 2 significant digits, not 3\nsignificant digits."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 3:35"}, "The prince of the fathers\u2019 house of the families of Merari was Zuriel the son of Abihail. They shall encamp on the north\nside of the tabernacle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 3:36"}, "The appointed duty of the sons of Merari shall be the tabernacle\u2019s boards, its bars, its pillars, its sockets, all its\ninstruments, all its service, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 3:37"}, "the pillars of the court around it, their sockets, their pins, and their cords.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 3:38"}, "Those who encamp before the tabernacle eastward, in front of the Tent of Meeting towards the sunrise, shall be Musa, and\nHarun and his sons, keeping the requirements of the sanctuary for the duty of the children of Israel. The outsider who comes\nnear shall be put to death. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 3:39"}, "All who were counted of the Levites, whom Musa and Harun counted at the commandment of the LORD, by their families, all\nthe males from a month old and upward, were twenty-two thousand.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 3:40"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cCount all the firstborn males of the children of Israel from a month old and upward, and take the\nnumber of their names. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 3:41"}, "You shall take the Levites for me\u2014I am the LORD\u2014instead of all the firstborn amongst the children of Israel; and the\nlivestock of the Levites instead of all the firstborn amongst the livestock of the children of Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 3:42"}, "Musa counted, as the LORD commanded him, all the firstborn amongst the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 3:43"}, "All the firstborn males according to the number of names from a month old and upward, of those who were counted of them,\nwere twenty-two thousand and two hundred and seventy-three. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 3:44"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 3:45"}, "\u201cTake the Levites instead of all the firstborn amongst the children of Israel, and the livestock of the Levites instead\nof their livestock; and the Levites shall be mine. I am the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 3:46"}, "For the redemption of the two hundred and seventy-three of the firstborn of the children of Israel who exceed the number\nof the Levites, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 3:47"}, "you shall take five shekels apiece for each one; according to the\nshekel", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of the sanctuary you shall take them (the shekel is twenty\ngerahs", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A gerah is about 0.5 grams or about 7.7\ngrains."]}], "caller": "+"}, "); \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 3:48"}, "and you shall give the money, with which their remainder is redeemed, to Harun and to his sons.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 3:49"}, "Musa took the redemption money from those who exceeded the number of those who were redeemed by the Levites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 3:50"}, "from the firstborn of the children of Israel he took the money, one thousand and three hundred and sixty-five\nshekels,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:50 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 1365 shekels is about 13.65 kilograms or about\n30 pounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " according to the shekel of the sanctuary; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "NUM 3:51"}, "and Musa gave the redemption money to Harun and to his sons, according to the LORD\u2019s word, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 4:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and to Harun, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 4:2"}, "\u201cTake a census of the sons of Kohath from amongst the sons of Levi, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 4:3"}, "from thirty years old and upward even until fifty years old, all who enter into the service to do the work in the Tent of\nMeeting. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 4:4"}, "\u201cThis is the service of the sons of Kohath in the Tent of Meeting, regarding the most holy things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 4:5"}, "When the camp moves forward, Harun shall go in with his sons; and they shall take down the veil of the screen, cover the\nark of the Testimony with it, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 4:6"}, "put a covering of sealskin on it, spread a blue cloth over it, and put in its poles.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 4:7"}, "\u201cOn the table of show bread they shall spread a blue cloth, and put on it the dishes, the spoons, the bowls, and the cups\nwith which to pour out; and the continual bread shall be on it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 4:8"}, "They shall spread on them a scarlet cloth, and cover it with a covering of sealskin, and shall put in its poles.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 4:9"}, "\u201cThey shall take a blue cloth and cover the lamp stand of the light, its lamps, its snuffers, its snuff dishes, and all\nits oil vessels, with which they minister to it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 4:10"}, "They shall put it and all its vessels within a covering of sealskin, and shall put it on the frame.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 4:11"}, "\u201cOn the golden altar they shall spread a blue cloth, and cover it with a covering of sealskin, and shall put in its\npoles. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 4:12"}, "\u201cThey shall take all the vessels of ministry with which they minister in the sanctuary, and put them in a blue cloth,\ncover them with a covering of sealskin, and shall put them on the frame.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 4:13"}, "\u201cThey shall take away the ashes from the altar, and spread a purple cloth on it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 4:14"}, "They shall put on it all its vessels with which they minister about it, the fire pans, the meat hooks, the shovels, and\nthe basins\u2014all the vessels of the altar; and they shall spread on it a covering of sealskin, and put in its poles.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 4:15"}, "\u201cWhen Harun and his sons have finished covering the sanctuary and all the furniture of the sanctuary, as the camp moves\nforward; after that, the sons of Kohath shall come to carry it; but they shall not touch the sanctuary, lest they die. The sons\nof Kohath shall carry these things belonging to the Tent of Meeting.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 4:16"}, "\u201cThe duty of Eleazar the son of Harun the priest shall be the oil for the light, the sweet incense, the continual meal\noffering, and the anointing oil, the requirements of all the tabernacle, and of all that is in it, the sanctuary, and its\nfurnishings.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 4:17"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and to Harun, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 4:18"}, "\u201cDon\u2019t cut off the tribe of the families of the Kohathites from amongst the Levites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 4:19"}, "but thus do to them, that they may live, and not die, when they approach the most holy things: Harun and his sons shall\ngo in and appoint everyone to his service and to his burden; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 4:20"}, "but they shall not go in to see the sanctuary even for a moment, lest they die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 4:21"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 4:22"}, "\u201cTake a census of the sons of Gershon also, by their fathers\u2019 houses, by their families;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 4:23"}, "you shall count them from thirty years old and upward until fifty years old: all who enter in to wait on the service, to\ndo the work in the Tent of Meeting. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 4:24"}, "\u201cThis is the service of the families of the Gershonites, in serving and in bearing burdens:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 4:25"}, "they shall carry the curtains of the tabernacle and the Tent of Meeting, its covering, the covering of sealskin that is\non it, the screen for the door of the Tent of Meeting, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 4:26"}, "the hangings of the court, the screen for the door of the gate of the court which is by the tabernacle and around the\naltar, their cords, and all the instruments of their service, and whatever shall be done with them. They shall serve in there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 4:27"}, "At the commandment of Harun and his sons shall be all the service of the sons of the Gershonites, in all their burden and\nin all their service; and you shall appoint their duty to them in all their responsibilities.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 4:28"}, "This is the service of the families of the sons of the Gershonites in the Tent of Meeting. Their duty shall be under the\nhand of Ithamar the son of Harun the priest. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 4:29"}, "\u201cAs for the sons of Merari, you shall count them by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 4:30"}, "you shall count them from thirty years old and upward even to fifty years old\u2014everyone who enters on the service, to do\nthe work of the Tent of Meeting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 4:31"}, "This is the duty of their burden, according to all their service in the Tent of Meeting: the tabernacle\u2019s boards, its\nbars, its pillars, its sockets, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 4:32"}, "the pillars of the court around it, their sockets, their pins, their cords, with all their instruments, and with all\ntheir service. You shall appoint the instruments of the duty of their burden to them by name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 4:33"}, "This is the service of the families of the sons of Merari, according to all their service in the Tent of Meeting, under\nthe hand of Ithamar the son of Harun the priest.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 4:34"}, "Musa and Harun and the princes of the congregation counted the sons of the Kohathites by their families, and by their\nfathers\u2019 houses, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 4:35"}, "from thirty years old and upward even to fifty years old, everyone who entered into the service for work in the Tent of\nMeeting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 4:36"}, "Those who were counted of them by their families were two thousand and seven hundred and fifty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 4:37"}, "These are those who were counted of the families of the Kohathites, all who served in the Tent of Meeting, whom Musa and\nHarun counted according to the commandment of the LORD by Musa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 4:38"}, "Those who were counted of the sons of Gershon, by their families, and by their fathers\u2019 houses,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 4:39"}, "from thirty years old and upward even to fifty years old\u2014everyone who entered into the service for work in the Tent of\nMeeting, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 4:40"}, "even those who were counted of them, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses, were two thousand and six hundred and\nthirty. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 4:41"}, "These are those who were counted of the families of the sons of Gershon, all who served in the Tent of Meeting, whom Musa\nand Harun counted according to the commandment of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 4:42"}, "Those who were counted of the families of the sons of Merari, by their families, by their fathers\u2019 houses,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 4:43"}, "from thirty years old and upward even to fifty years old\u2014everyone who entered into the service for work in the Tent of\nMeeting, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 4:44"}, "even those who were counted of them by their families, were three thousand and two hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 4:45"}, "These are those who were counted of the families of the sons of Merari, whom Musa and Harun counted according to the\ncommandment of the LORD by Musa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 4:46"}, "All those who were counted of the Levites whom Musa and Harun and the princes of Israel counted, by their families and by\ntheir fathers\u2019 houses, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 4:47"}, "from thirty years old and upward even to fifty years old, everyone who entered in to do the work of service and the work\nof bearing burdens in the Tent of Meeting, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 4:48"}, "even those who were counted of them, were eight thousand and five hundred and eighty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 4:49"}, "According to the commandment of the LORD they were counted by Musa, everyone according to his service and according to\nhis burden. Thus they were counted by him, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 5:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 5:2"}, "\u201cCommand the children of Israel that they put out of the camp every leper, everyone who has a discharge, and whoever is\nunclean by a corpse. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 5:3"}, "You shall put both male and female outside of the camp so that they don\u2019t defile their camp, in the midst of which I\ndwell.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 5:4"}, "The children of Israel did so, and put them outside of the camp; as the LORD spoke to Musa, so the children of Israel did.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 5:5"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 5:6"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel: \u2018When a man or woman commits any sin that men commit, so as to trespass against the\nLORD, and that soul is guilty, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 5:7"}, "then he shall confess his sin which he has done; and he shall make restitution for his guilt in full, add to it the fifth\npart of it, and give it to him in respect of whom he has been guilty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 5:8"}, "But if the man has no kinsman to whom restitution may be made for the guilt, the restitution for guilt which is made to\nthe LORD shall be the priest\u2019s, in addition to the ram of the atonement, by which atonement shall be made for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 5:9"}, "Every heave offering of all the holy things of the children of Israel, which they present to the priest, shall be his.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 5:10"}, "Every man\u2019s holy things shall be his; whatever any man gives the priest, it shall be his.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 5:11"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 5:12"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and tell them: \u2018If any man\u2019s wife goes astray and is unfaithful to him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 5:13"}, "and a man lies with her carnally, and it is hidden from the eyes of her husband and this is kept concealed, and she is\ndefiled, there is no witness against her, and she isn\u2019t taken in the act;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 5:14"}, "and the spirit of jealousy comes on him, and he is jealous of his wife and she is defiled; or if the spirit of jealousy\ncomes on him, and he is jealous of his wife and she isn\u2019t defiled;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 5:15"}, "then the man shall bring his wife to the priest, and shall bring her offering for her: one tenth of an\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of barley meal. He shall pour no oil on it, nor put frankincense on it, for it is a meal offering of jealousy, a meal\noffering of memorial, bringing iniquity to memory. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 5:16"}, "The priest shall bring her near, and set her before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 5:17"}, "The priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel; and the priest shall take some of the dust that is on the floor of\nthe tabernacle and put it into the water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 5:18"}, "The priest shall set the woman before the LORD, and let the hair of the woman\u2019s head go loose, and put the meal offering\nof memorial in her hands, which is the meal offering of jealousy. The priest shall have in his hand the water of bitterness\nthat brings a curse. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 5:19"}, "The priest shall cause her to take an oath and shall tell the woman, \u201cIf no man has lain with you, and if you haven\u2019t\ngone aside to uncleanness, being under your husband\u2019s authority, be free from this water of bitterness that brings a curse.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 5:20"}, "But if you have gone astray, being under your husband\u2019s authority, and if you are defiled, and some man has lain with you\nbesides your husband\u2014\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 5:21"}, "then the priest shall cause the woman to swear with the oath of cursing, and the priest shall tell the woman, \u201cMay The\nLORD make you a curse and an oath amongst your people, when the LORD allows your thigh to fall away, and your body to swell;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 5:22"}, "and this water that brings a curse will go into your bowels, and make your body swell, and your thigh fall away.\u201d The\nwoman shall say, \u201cAmen, Amen.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 5:23"}, "\u201c\u2018The priest shall write these curses in a book, and he shall wipe them into the water of bitterness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 5:24"}, "He shall make the woman drink the water of bitterness that causes the curse; and the water that causes the curse shall\nenter into her and become bitter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 5:25"}, "The priest shall take the meal offering of jealousy out of the woman\u2019s hand, and shall wave the meal offering before the\nLORD, and bring it to the altar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 5:26"}, "The priest shall take a handful of the meal offering, as its memorial portion, and burn it on the altar, and afterward\nshall make the woman drink the water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 5:27"}, "When he has made her drink the water, then it shall happen, if she is defiled and has committed a trespass against her\nhusband, that the water that causes the curse will enter into her and become bitter, and her body will swell, and her thigh\nwill fall away; and the woman will be a curse amongst her people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 5:28"}, "If the woman isn\u2019t defiled, but is clean; then she shall be free, and shall conceive\noffspring.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 5:29"}, "\u201c\u2018This is the law of jealousy, when a wife, being under her husband, goes astray, and is defiled,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 5:30"}, "or when the spirit of jealousy comes on a man, and he is jealous of his wife; then he shall set the woman before the\nLORD, and the priest shall execute on her all this law. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 5:31"}, "The man shall be free from iniquity, and that woman shall bear her iniquity.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 6:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 6:2"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and tell them: \u2018When either man or woman shall make a special vow, the vow of a\nNazirite, to separate himself to the LORD, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 6:3"}, "he shall separate himself from wine and strong drink. He shall drink no vinegar of wine, or vinegar of fermented drink,\nneither shall he drink any juice of grapes, nor eat fresh grapes or dried.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 6:4"}, "All the days of his separation he shall eat nothing that is made of the grapevine, from the seeds even to the skins.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 6:5"}, "\u201c\u2018All the days of his vow of separation no razor shall come on his head, until the days are fulfilled in which he\nseparates himself to the LORD. He shall be holy. He shall let the locks of the hair of his head grow long.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 6:6"}, "\u201c\u2018All the days that he separates himself to the LORD he shall not go near a dead body.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 6:7"}, "He shall not make himself unclean for his father, or for his mother, for his brother, or for his sister, when they die,\nbecause his separation to Allah ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " is on his head. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 6:8"}, "All the days of his separation he is holy to the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 6:9"}, "\u201c\u2018If any man dies very suddenly beside him, and he defiles the head of his separation, then he shall shave his head in the\nday of his cleansing. On the seventh day he shall shave it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 6:10"}, "On the eighth day he shall bring two turtledoves or two young pigeons to the priest, to the door of the Tent of Meeting.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 6:11"}, "The priest shall offer one for a sin offering, and the other for a burnt offering, and make atonement for him, because he\nsinned by reason of the dead, and shall make his head holy that same day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 6:12"}, "He shall separate to the LORD the days of his separation, and shall bring a male lamb a year old for a trespass offering;\nbut the former days shall be void, because his separation was defiled.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 6:13"}, "\u201c\u2018This is the law of the Nazirite: when the days of his separation are fulfilled, he shall be brought to the door of the\nTent of Meeting, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 6:14"}, "and he shall offer his offering to the LORD: one male lamb a year old without defect for a burnt offering, one ewe lamb a\nyear old without defect for a sin offering, one ram without defect for peace offerings,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 6:15"}, "a basket of unleavened bread, cakes of fine flour mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers anointed with oil with their meal\noffering and their drink offerings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 6:16"}, "The priest shall present them before the LORD, and shall offer his sin offering and his burnt offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 6:17"}, "He shall offer the ram for a sacrifice of peace offerings to the LORD, with the basket of unleavened bread. The priest\nshall offer also its meal offering and its drink offering. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 6:18"}, "The Nazirite shall shave the head of his separation at the door of the Tent of Meeting, take the hair of the head of his\nseparation, and put it on the fire which is under the sacrifice of peace offerings.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 6:19"}, "The priest shall take the boiled shoulder of the ram, one unleavened cake out of the basket, and one unleavened wafer,\nand shall put them on the hands of the Nazirite after he has shaved the head of his separation;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 6:20"}, "and the priest shall wave them for a wave offering before the LORD. They are holy for the priest, together with the\nbreast that is waved and the thigh that is offered. After that the Nazirite may drink wine.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 6:21"}, "\u201c\u2018This is the law of the Nazirite who vows and of his offering to the LORD for his separation, in addition to that which\nhe is able to afford. According to his vow which he vows, so he must do after the law of his separation.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 6:22"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 6:23"}, "\u201cSpeak to Harun and to his sons, saying, \u2018This is how you shall bless the children of Israel.\u2019 You shall tell them,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 6:24"}, "\u2018The LORD bless you, and keep you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 6:25"}, "The LORD make his face to shine on you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and be gracious to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 6:26"}, "The LORD lift up his face towards you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and give you peace.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 6:27"}, "\u201cSo they shall put my name on the children of Israel; and I will bless them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 7:1"}, "On the day that Musa had finished setting up the tabernacle, and had anointed it and sanctified it with all its furniture,\nand the altar with all its vessels, and had anointed and sanctified them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 7:2"}, "the princes of Israel, the heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, offered. These were the princes of the tribes. These are they\nwho were over those who were counted; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 7:3"}, "and they brought their offering before the LORD, six covered wagons and twelve oxen; a wagon for every two of the princes,\nand for each one an ox. They presented them before the tabernacle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 7:4"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 7:5"}, "\u201cAccept these from them, that they may be used in doing the service of the Tent of Meeting; and you shall give them to the\nLevites, to every man according to his service.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 7:6"}, "Musa took the wagons and the oxen, and gave them to the Levites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 7:7"}, "He gave two wagons and four oxen to the sons of Gershon, according to their service.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 7:8"}, "He gave four wagons and eight oxen to the sons of Merari, according to their service, under the direction of Ithamar the\nson of Harun the priest. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 7:9"}, "But to the sons of Kohath he gave none, because the service of the sanctuary belonged to them; they carried it on their\nshoulders. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 7:10"}, "The princes gave offerings for the dedication of the altar in the day that it was anointed. The princes gave their\nofferings before the altar. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 7:11"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cThey shall offer their offering, each prince on his day, for the dedication of the altar.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 7:12"}, "He who offered his offering the first day was Nahshon the son of Amminadab, of the tribe of Judah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 7:13"}, "and his offering was: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty\nshekels,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 7:14"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 7:15"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 7:16"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 7:17"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Nahshon the son of Amminadab. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 7:18"}, "On the second day Nethanel the son of Zuar, prince of Issachar, gave his offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 7:19"}, "He offered for his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 7:20"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 7:21"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 7:22"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 7:23"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Nethanel the son of Zuar. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 7:24"}, "On the third day Eliab the son of Helon, prince of the children of Zebulun,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 7:25"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was a hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 7:26"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 7:27"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 7:28"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 7:29"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Eliab the son of Helon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 7:30"}, "On the fourth day Elizur the son of Shedeur, prince of the children of Reuben,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 7:31"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 7:32"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 7:33"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 7:34"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 7:35"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Elizur the son of Shedeur. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 7:36"}, "On the fifth day Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai, prince of the children of Simeon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 7:37"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 7:38"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 7:39"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 7:40"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 7:41"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old:\nthis was the offering of Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 7:42"}, "On the sixth day, Eliasaph the son of Deuel, prince of the children of Gad,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 7:43"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 7:44"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 7:45"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 7:46"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 7:47"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Eliasaph the son of Deuel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 7:48"}, "On the seventh day Elishama the son of Ammihud, prince of the children of Ephraim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 7:49"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 7:50"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "NUM 7:51"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "NUM 7:52"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "NUM 7:53"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Elishama the son of Ammihud. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "NUM 7:54"}, "On the eighth day Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur, prince of the children of Manasseh,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "NUM 7:55"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "NUM 7:56"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "NUM 7:57"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "NUM 7:58"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "NUM 7:59"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "NUM 7:60"}, "On the ninth day Abidan the son of Gideoni, prince of the children of Benjamin,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "NUM 7:61"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "NUM 7:62"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "NUM 7:63"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "NUM 7:64"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "NUM 7:65"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Abidan the son of Gideoni. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "NUM 7:66"}, "On the tenth day Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai, prince of the children of Dan,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "NUM 7:67"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "68", "sid": "NUM 7:68"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "69", "sid": "NUM 7:69"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "70", "sid": "NUM 7:70"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "71", "sid": "NUM 7:71"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "72", "sid": "NUM 7:72"}, "On the eleventh day Pagiel the son of Ochran, prince of the children of Asher,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "73", "sid": "NUM 7:73"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "74", "sid": "NUM 7:74"}, "one golden ladle of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "75", "sid": "NUM 7:75"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "76", "sid": "NUM 7:76"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "77", "sid": "NUM 7:77"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Pagiel the son of Ochran. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "78", "sid": "NUM 7:78"}, "On the twelfth day Ahira the son of Enan, prince of the children of Naphtali,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "79", "sid": "NUM 7:79"}, "gave his offering: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver platter, the weight of which was one hundred and thirty shekels,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one silver bowl of seventy shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mixed with oil\nfor a meal offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "80", "sid": "NUM 7:80"}, "one golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "81", "sid": "NUM 7:81"}, "one young bull, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one ram, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["one male lamb a year old, for a burnt offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "82", "sid": "NUM 7:82"}, "one male goat for a sin offering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "83", "sid": "NUM 7:83"}, "and for the sacrifice of peace offerings, two head of cattle, five rams, five male goats, and five male lambs a year old.\nThis was the offering of Ahira the son of Enan. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "84", "sid": "NUM 7:84"}, "This was the dedication offering of the altar, on the day when it was anointed, by the princes of Israel: twelve silver\nplatters, twelve silver bowls, twelve golden ladles; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "85", "sid": "NUM 7:85"}, "each silver platter weighing one hundred and thirty shekels, and each bowl seventy; all the silver of the vessels two\nthousand and four hundred shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "86", "sid": "NUM 7:86"}, "the twelve golden ladles, full of incense, weighing ten shekels apiece, according to the shekel of the sanctuary; all the\ngold of the ladles weighed one hundred and twenty shekels; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "87", "sid": "NUM 7:87"}, "all the cattle for the burnt offering twelve bulls, the rams twelve, the male lambs a year old twelve, and their meal\noffering; and twelve male goats for a sin offering; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "88", "sid": "NUM 7:88"}, "and all the cattle for the sacrifice of peace offerings: twenty-four bulls, sixty rams, sixty male goats, and sixty male\nlambs a year old. This was the dedication offering of the altar, after it was anointed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "89", "sid": "NUM 7:89"}, "When Musa went into the Tent of Meeting to speak with the LORD, he heard his voice speaking to him from above the mercy\nseat that was on the ark of the Testimony, from between the two cherubim; and he spoke to him.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 8:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 8:2"}, "\u201cSpeak to Harun, and tell him, \u2018When you light the lamps, the seven lamps shall give light in front of the lamp stand.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 8:3"}, "Harun did so. He lit its lamps to light the area in front of the lamp stand, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 8:4"}, "This was the workmanship of the lamp stand, beaten work of gold. From its base to its flowers, it was beaten work. He made\nthe lamp stand according to the pattern which the LORD had shown Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 8:5"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 8:6"}, "\u201cTake the Levites from amongst the children of Israel, and cleanse them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 8:7"}, "You shall do this to them, to cleanse them: sprinkle the water of cleansing on them, let them shave their whole bodies\nwith a razor, let them wash their clothes, and cleanse themselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 8:8"}, "Then let them take a young bull and its meal offering, fine flour mixed with oil; and another young bull you shall take\nfor a sin offering. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 8:9"}, "You shall present the Levites before the Tent of Meeting. You shall assemble the whole congregation of the children of\nIsrael. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 8:10"}, "You shall present the Levites before the LORD. The children of Israel shall lay their hands on the Levites,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 8:11"}, "and Harun shall offer the Levites before the LORD for a wave offering on the behalf of the children of Israel, that it\nmay be theirs to do the service of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 8:12"}, "\u201cThe Levites shall lay their hands on the heads of the bulls, and you shall offer the one for a sin offering and the\nother for a burnt offering to the LORD, to make atonement for the Levites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 8:13"}, "You shall set the Levites before Harun and before his sons, and offer them as a wave offering to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 8:14"}, "Thus you shall separate the Levites from amongst the children of Israel, and the Levites shall be mine.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 8:15"}, "\u201cAfter that, the Levites shall go in to do the service of the Tent of Meeting. You shall cleanse them, and offer them as\na wave offering. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 8:16"}, "For they are wholly given to me from amongst the children of Israel; instead of all who open the womb, even the firstborn\nof all the children of Israel, I have taken them to me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 8:17"}, "For all the firstborn amongst the children of Israel are mine, both man and animal. On the day that I struck all the\nfirstborn in the land of Egypt, I sanctified them for myself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 8:18"}, "I have taken the Levites instead of all the firstborn amongst the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 8:19"}, "I have given the Levites as a gift to Harun and to his sons from amongst the children of Israel, to do the service of the\nchildren of Israel in the Tent of Meeting, and to make atonement for the children of Israel, so that there will be no plague\namongst the children of Israel when the children of Israel come near to the sanctuary.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 8:20"}, "Musa, and Harun, and all the congregation of the children of Israel did so to the Levites. According to all that the LORD\ncommanded Musa concerning the Levites, so the children of Israel did to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 8:21"}, "The Levites purified themselves from sin, and they washed their clothes; and Harun offered them for a wave offering\nbefore the LORD and Harun made atonement for them to cleanse them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 8:22"}, "After that, the Levites went in to do their service in the Tent of Meeting before Harun and before his sons: as the LORD\nhad commanded Musa concerning the Levites, so they did to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 8:23"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 8:24"}, "\u201cThis is what is assigned to the Levites: from twenty-five years old and upward they shall go in to wait on the service\nin the work of the Tent of Meeting; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 8:25"}, "and from the age of fifty years they shall retire from doing the work, and shall serve no more,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 8:26"}, "but shall assist their brothers in the Tent of Meeting, to perform the duty, and shall perform no service. This is how\nyou shall have the Levites do their duties.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 9:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa in the wilderness of Sinai, in the first month of the second year after they had come out of the\nland of Egypt, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 9:2"}, "\u201cLet the children of Israel keep the Passover in its appointed season.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 9:3"}, "On the fourteenth day of this month, at evening, you shall keep it in its appointed season. You shall keep it according to\nall its statutes and according to all its ordinances.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 9:4"}, "Musa told the children of Israel that they should keep the Passover.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 9:5"}, "They kept the Passover in the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at evening, in the wilderness of Sinai.\nAccording to all that the LORD commanded Musa, so the children of Israel did.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 9:6"}, "There were certain men, who were unclean because of the dead body of a man, so that they could not keep the Passover on\nthat day, and they came before Musa and Harun on that day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 9:7"}, "Those men said to him, \u201cWe are unclean because of the dead body of a man. Why are we kept back, that we may not offer the\noffering of the LORD in its appointed season amongst the children of Israel?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 9:8"}, "Musa answered them, \u201cWait, that I may hear what the LORD will command concerning you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 9:9"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 9:10"}, "\u201cSay to the children of Israel, \u2018If any man of you or of your generations is unclean by reason of a dead body, or is on a\njourney far away, he shall still keep the Passover to the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 9:11"}, "In the second month, on the fourteenth day at evening they shall keep it; they shall eat it with unleavened bread and\nbitter herbs. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 9:12"}, "They shall leave none of it until the morning, nor break a bone of it. According to all the statute of the Passover they\nshall keep it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 9:13"}, "But the man who is clean, and is not on a journey, and fails to keep the Passover, that soul shall be cut off from his\npeople. Because he didn\u2019t offer the offering of the LORD in its appointed season, that man shall bear his sin.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 9:14"}, "\u201c\u2018If a foreigner lives amongst you, and desires to keep the Passover to the LORD, then he shall do so according to the\nstatute of the Passover, and according to its ordinance. You shall have one statute, both for the foreigner, and for him who is\nborn in the land.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 9:15"}, "On the day that the tabernacle was raised up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, even the Tent of the Testimony. At\nevening it was over the tabernacle, as it were the appearance of fire, until morning.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 9:16"}, "So it was continually. The cloud covered it, and the appearance of fire by night.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 9:17"}, "Whenever the cloud was taken up from over the Tent, then after that the children of Israel travelled; and in the place\nwhere the cloud remained, there the children of Israel encamped.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 9:18"}, "At the commandment of the LORD, the children of Israel travelled, and at the commandment of the LORD they encamped. As\nlong as the cloud remained on the tabernacle they remained encamped.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 9:19"}, "When the cloud stayed on the tabernacle many days, then the children of Israel kept the LORD\u2019s command, and didn\u2019t\ntravel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 9:20"}, "Sometimes the cloud was a few days on the tabernacle; then according to the commandment of the LORD they remained\nencamped, and according to the commandment of the LORD they travelled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 9:21"}, "Sometimes the cloud was from evening until morning; and when the cloud was taken up in the morning, they travelled; or by\nday and by night, when the cloud was taken up, they travelled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 9:22"}, "Whether it was two days, or a month, or a year that the cloud stayed on the tabernacle, remaining on it, the children of\nIsrael remained encamped, and didn\u2019t travel; but when it was taken up, they travelled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 9:23"}, "At the commandment of the LORD they encamped, and at the commandment of the LORD they travelled. They kept the LORD\u2019s\ncommand, at the commandment of the LORD by Musa. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 10:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 10:2"}, "\u201cMake two trumpets of silver. You shall make them of beaten work. You shall use them for the calling of the congregation,\nand for the journeying of the camps. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 10:3"}, "When they blow them, all the congregation shall gather themselves to you at the door of the Tent of Meeting.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 10:4"}, "If they blow just one, then the princes, the heads of the thousands of Israel, shall gather themselves to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 10:5"}, "When you blow an alarm, the camps that lie on the east side shall go forward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 10:6"}, "When you blow an alarm the second time, the camps that lie on the south side shall go forward. They shall blow an alarm\nfor their journeys. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 10:7"}, "But when the assembly is to be gathered together, you shall blow, but you shall not sound an alarm.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 10:8"}, "\u201cThe sons of Harun, the priests, shall blow the trumpets. This shall be to you for a statute forever throughout your\ngenerations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 10:9"}, "When you go to war in your land against the adversary who oppresses you, then you shall sound an alarm with the trumpets.\nThen you will be remembered before Allah your LORD, and you will be saved from your enemies.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 10:10"}, "\u201cAlso in the day of your gladness, and in your set feasts, and in the beginnings of your months, you shall blow the\ntrumpets over your burnt offerings, and over the sacrifices of your peace offerings; and they shall be to you for a memorial\nbefore your Allah. I am Allah your LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 10:11"}, "In the second year, in the second month, on the twentieth day of the month, the cloud was taken up from over the\ntabernacle of the covenant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 10:12"}, "The children of Israel went forward on their journeys out of the wilderness of Sinai; and the cloud stayed in the\nwilderness of Paran. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 10:13"}, "They first went forward according to the commandment of the LORD by Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 10:14"}, "First, the standard of the camp of the children of Judah went forward according to their armies. Nahshon the son of\nAmminadab was over his army. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 10:15"}, "Nethanel the son of Zuar was over the army of the tribe of the children of Issachar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 10:16"}, "Eliab the son of Helon was over the army of the tribe of the children of Zebulun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 10:17"}, "The tabernacle was taken down; and the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari, who bore the tabernacle, went forward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 10:18"}, "The standard of the camp of Reuben went forward according to their armies. Elizur the son of Shedeur was over his army.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 10:19"}, "Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai was over the army of the tribe of the children of Simeon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 10:20"}, "Eliasaph the son of Deuel was over the army of the tribe of the children of Gad.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 10:21"}, "The Kohathites set forward, bearing the sanctuary. The others set up the tabernacle before they arrived.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 10:22"}, "The standard of the camp of the children of Ephraim set forward according to their armies. Elishama the son of Ammihud\nwas over his army. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 10:23"}, "Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur was over the army of the tribe of the children of Manasseh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 10:24"}, "Abidan the son of Gideoni was over the army of the tribe of the children of Benjamin.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 10:25"}, "The standard of the camp of the children of Dan, which was the rear guard of all the camps, set forward according to\ntheir armies. Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai was over his army. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 10:26"}, "Pagiel the son of Ochran was over the army of the tribe of the children of Asher.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 10:27"}, "Ahira the son of Enan was over the army of the tribe of the children of Naphtali.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 10:28"}, "Thus were the travels of the children of Israel according to their armies; and they went forward.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 10:29"}, "Musa said to Hobab, the son of Reuel the Midianite, Musa\u2019s father-in-law, \u201cWe are journeying to the place of which the\nLORD said, \u2018I will give it to you.\u2019 Come with us, and we will treat you well; for the LORD has spoken good concerning Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 10:30"}, "He said to him, \u201cI will not go; but I will depart to my own land, and to my relatives.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 10:31"}, "Musa said, \u201cDon\u2019t leave us, please; because you know how we are to encamp in the wilderness, and you can be our eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 10:32"}, "It shall be, if you go with us\u2014yes, it shall be\u2014that whatever good the LORD does to us, we will do the same to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 10:33"}, "They set forward from the Mount of the LORD three days\u2019 journey. The ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant went before them three\ndays\u2019 journey, to seek out a resting place for them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 10:34"}, "The cloud of the LORD was over them by day, when they set forward from the camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 10:35"}, "When the ark went forward, Musa said, \u201cRise up, LORD, and let your enemies be scattered! Let those who hate you flee\nbefore you!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 10:36"}, "When it rested, he said, \u201cReturn, LORD, to the ten thousands of the thousands of Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 11:1"}, "The people were complaining in the ears of the LORD. When the LORD heard it, his anger burnt; and the LORD\u2019s fire burnt\namongst them, and consumed some of the outskirts of the camp. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 11:2"}, "The people cried to Musa; and Musa prayed to the LORD, and the fire abated.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 11:3"}, "The name of that place was called Taberah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Taberah means \u201cburning\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " because the LORD\u2019s fire burnt amongst them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 11:4"}, "The mixed multitude that was amongst them lusted exceedingly; and the children of Israel also wept again, and said, \u201cWho\nwill give us meat to eat? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 11:5"}, "We remember the fish, which we ate in Egypt for nothing; the cucumbers, and the melons, and the leeks, and the onions, and\nthe garlic; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 11:6"}, "but now we have lost our appetite. There is nothing at all except this manna to look at.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 11:7"}, "The manna was like coriander seed, and it looked like bdellium.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Bdellium is a resin extracted from certain African trees."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 11:8"}, "The people went around, gathered it, and ground it in mills, or beat it in mortars, and boiled it in pots, and made cakes\nof it. Its taste was like the taste of fresh oil. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 11:9"}, "When the dew fell on the camp in the night, the manna fell on it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 11:10"}, "Musa heard the people weeping throughout their families, every man at the door of his tent; and the LORD\u2019s anger burnt\ngreatly; and Musa was displeased. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 11:11"}, "Musa said to the LORD, \u201cWhy have you treated your servant so badly? Why haven\u2019t I found favour in your sight, that you\nlay the burden of all this people on me? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 11:12"}, "Have I conceived all this people? Have I brought them out, that you should tell me, \u2018Carry them in your bosom, as a nurse\ncarries a nursing infant, to the land which you swore to their fathers?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 11:13"}, "Where could I get meat to give all these people? For they weep before me, saying, \u2018Give us meat, that we may eat.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 11:14"}, "I am not able to bear all this people alone, because it is too heavy for me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 11:15"}, "If you treat me this way, please kill me right now, if I have found favour in your sight; and don\u2019t let me see my\nwretchedness.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 11:16"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cGather to me seventy men of the elders of Israel, whom you know to be the elders of the people\nand officers over them; and bring them to the Tent of Meeting, that they may stand there with you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 11:17"}, "I will come down and talk with you there. I will take of the Spirit which is on you, and will put it on them; and they\nshall bear the burden of the people with you, that you don\u2019t bear it yourself alone.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 11:18"}, "\u201cSay to the people, \u2018Sanctify yourselves in preparation for tomorrow, and you will eat meat; for you have wept in the\nears of the LORD, saying, \u201cWho will give us meat to eat? For it was well with us in Egypt.\u201d Therefore the LORD will give you\nmeat, and you will eat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 11:19"}, "You will not eat just one day, or two days, or five days, or ten days, or twenty days,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 11:20"}, "but a whole month, until it comes out at your nostrils, and it is loathsome to you; because you have rejected the LORD\nwho is amongst you, and have wept before him, saying, \u201cWhy did we come out of Egypt?\u201d\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 11:21"}, "Musa said, \u201cThe people, amongst whom I am, are six hundred thousand men on foot; and you have said, \u2018I will give them\nmeat, that they may eat a whole month.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 11:22"}, "Shall flocks and herds be slaughtered for them, to be sufficient for them? Shall all the fish of the sea be gathered\ntogether for them, to be sufficient for them?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 11:23"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cHas the LORD\u2019s hand grown short? Now you will see whether my word will happen to you or not.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 11:24"}, "Musa went out, and told the people the LORD\u2019s words; and he gathered seventy men of the elders of the people, and set\nthem around the Tent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 11:25"}, "The LORD came down in the cloud, and spoke to him, and took of the Spirit that was on him, and put it on the seventy\nelders. When the Spirit rested on them, they prophesied, but they did so no more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 11:26"}, "But two men remained in the camp. The name of one was Eldad, and the name of the other Medad; and the Spirit rested on\nthem. They were of those who were written, but had not gone out to the Tent; and they prophesied in the camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 11:27"}, "A young man ran, and told Musa, and said, \u201cEldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 11:28"}, "Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of Musa, one of his chosen men, answered, \u201cMy lord Musa, forbid them!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 11:29"}, "Musa said to him, \u201cAre you jealous for my sake? I wish that all the LORD\u2019s people were prophets, that the LORD would put\nhis Spirit on them!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 11:30"}, "Musa went into the camp, he and the elders of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 11:31"}, "A wind from the LORD went out and brought quails from the sea, and let them fall by the camp, about a day\u2019s journey on\nthis side, and a day\u2019s journey on the other side, around the camp, and about two\ncubits", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " above the surface of the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 11:32"}, "The people rose up all that day, and all of that night, and all the next day, and gathered the quails. He who gathered\nleast gathered ten homers; ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 homer is about 220 litres or 6\nbushels"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and they spread them all out for themselves around the camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 11:33"}, "While the meat was still between their teeth, before it was chewed, the LORD\u2019s anger burnt against the people, and the\nLORD struck the people with a very great plague. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 11:34"}, "The name of that place was called Kibroth Hattaavah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:34\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Kibroth Hattaavah means \u201cgraves of lust\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " because there they buried the people who lusted.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 11:35"}, "From Kibroth Hattaavah the people travelled to Hazeroth; and they stayed at Hazeroth.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 12:1"}, "Miriam and Harun spoke against Musa because of the Cushite woman whom he had married; for he had married a Cushite woman.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 12:2"}, "They said, \u201cHas the LORD indeed spoken only with Musa? Hasn\u2019t he spoken also with us?\u201d And the LORD heard it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 12:3"}, "Now the man Musa was very humble, more than all the men who were on the surface of the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 12:4"}, "The LORD spoke suddenly to Musa, to Harun, and to Miriam, \u201cYou three come out to the Tent of Meeting!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The three of them came out. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 12:5"}, "The LORD came down in a pillar of cloud, and stood at the door of the Tent, and called Harun and Miriam; and they both\ncame forward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 12:6"}, "He said, \u201cNow hear my words. If there is a prophet amongst you, I, the LORD, will make myself known to him in a vision. I\nwill speak with him in a dream. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 12:7"}, "My servant Musa is not so. He is faithful in all my house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 12:8"}, "With him, I will speak mouth to mouth, even plainly, and not in riddles; and he shall see the LORD\u2019s form. Why then were\nyou not afraid to speak against my servant, against Musa?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 12:9"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against them; and he departed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 12:10"}, "The cloud departed from over the Tent; and behold, Miriam was leprous, as white as snow. Harun looked at Miriam, and\nbehold, she was leprous. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 12:11"}, "Harun said to Musa, \u201cOh, my lord, please don\u2019t count this sin against us, in which we have done foolishly, and in which\nwe have sinned. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 12:12"}, "Let her not, I pray, be as one dead, of whom the flesh is half consumed when he comes out of his mother\u2019s womb.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 12:13"}, "Musa cried to the LORD, saying, \u201cHeal her, Allah, I beg you!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 12:14"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cIf her father had but spit in her face, shouldn\u2019t she be ashamed seven days? Let her be shut up\noutside of the camp seven days, and after that she shall be brought in again.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 12:15"}, "Miriam was shut up outside of the camp seven days, and the people didn\u2019t travel until Miriam was brought in again.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 12:16"}, "Afterward the people travelled from Hazeroth, and encamped in the wilderness of Paran.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 13:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 13:2"}, "\u201cSend men, that they may spy out the land of Canaan, which I give to the children of Israel. Of every tribe of their\nfathers, you shall send a man, every one a prince amongst them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 13:3"}, "Musa sent them from the wilderness of Paran according to the commandment of the LORD. All of them were men who were heads\nof the children of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 13:4"}, "These were their names: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": ["Of the tribe of Reuben, Shammua the son of Zaccur. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 13:5"}, "Of the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat the son of Hori. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 13:6"}, "Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 13:7"}, "Of the tribe of Issachar, Igal the son of Yusuf. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 13:8"}, "Of the tribe of Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Nun. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 13:9"}, "Of the tribe of Benjamin, Palti the son of Raphu. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 13:10"}, "Of the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel the son of Sodi. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 13:11"}, "Of the tribe of Yusuf, of the tribe of Manasseh, Gaddi the son of Susi.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 13:12"}, "Of the tribe of Dan, Ammiel the son of Gemalli. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 13:13"}, "Of the tribe of Asher, Sethur the son of Michael. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 13:14"}, "Of the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi the son of Vophsi. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 13:15"}, "Of the tribe of Gad, Geuel the son of Machi. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 13:16"}, "These are the names of the men who Musa sent to spy out the land. Musa called Hoshea the son of Nun Joshua.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 13:17"}, "Musa sent them to spy out the land of Canaan, and said to them, \u201cGo up this way by the South, and go up into the hill\ncountry. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 13:18"}, "See the land, what it is; and the people who dwell therein, whether they are strong or weak, whether they are few or\nmany; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 13:19"}, "and what the land is that they dwell in, whether it is good or bad; and what cities they are that they dwell in, whether\nin camps, or in strongholds; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 13:20"}, "and what the land is, whether it is fertile or poor, whether there is wood therein, or not. Be courageous, and bring some\nof the fruit of the land.\u201d Now the time was the time of the first-ripe grapes.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 13:21"}, "So they went up, and spied out the land from the wilderness of Zin to Rehob, to the entrance of Hamath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 13:22"}, "They went up by the South, and came to Hebron; and Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the children of Anak, were there. (Now\nHebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.) \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 13:23"}, "They came to the valley of Eshcol, and cut down from there a branch with one cluster of grapes, and they bore it on a\nstaff between two. They also brought some of the pomegranates and figs.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 13:24"}, "That place was called the valley of Eshcol, because of the cluster which the children of Israel cut down from there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 13:25"}, "They returned from spying out the land at the end of forty days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 13:26"}, "They went and came to Musa, to Harun, and to all the congregation of the children of Israel, to the wilderness of Paran,\nto Kadesh; and brought back word to them and to all the congregation. They showed them the fruit of the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 13:27"}, "They told him, and said, \u201cWe came to the land where you sent us. Surely it flows with milk and honey, and this is its\nfruit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 13:28"}, "However, the people who dwell in the land are strong, and the cities are fortified and very large. Moreover, we saw the\nchildren of Anak there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 13:29"}, "Amalek dwells in the land of the South. The Hittite, the Jebusite, and the Amorite dwell in the hill country. The\nCanaanite dwells by the sea, and along the side of the Jordan.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 13:30"}, "Caleb stilled the people before Musa, and said, \u201cLet\u2019s go up at once, and possess it; for we are well able to overcome\nit!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 13:31"}, "But the men who went up with him said, \u201cWe aren\u2019t able to go up against the people; for they are stronger than we.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 13:32"}, "They brought up an evil report of the land which they had spied out to the children of Israel, saying, \u201cThe land, through\nwhich we have gone to spy it out, is a land that eats up its inhabitants; and all the people who we saw in it are men of great\nstature. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 13:33"}, "There we saw the Nephilim,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, giants"]}], "caller": "+"}, " the sons of Anak, who come from the\nNephilim.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, giants"]}], "caller": "+"}, " We were in our own sight as grasshoppers, and so we were in their sight.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 14:1"}, "All the congregation lifted up their voice, and cried; and the people wept that night.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 14:2"}, "All the children of Israel murmured against Musa and against Harun. The whole congregation said to them, \u201cWe wish that we\nhad died in the land of Egypt, or that we had died in this wilderness!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 14:3"}, "Why does the LORD bring us to this land, to fall by the sword? Our wives and our little ones will be captured or killed!\nWouldn\u2019t it be better for us to return into Egypt?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 14:4"}, "They said to one another, \u201cLet\u2019s choose a leader, and let\u2019s return into Egypt.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 14:5"}, "Then Musa and Harun fell on their faces before all the assembly of the congregation of the children of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 14:6"}, "Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh, who were of those who spied out the land, tore their clothes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 14:7"}, "They spoke to all the congregation of the children of Israel, saying, \u201cThe land, which we passed through to spy it out, is\nan exceedingly good land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 14:8"}, "If the LORD delights in us, then he will bring us into this land, and give it to us: a land which flows with milk and\nhoney. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 14:9"}, "Only don\u2019t rebel against the LORD, neither fear the people of the land; for they are bread for us. Their defence is\nremoved from over them, and the LORD is with us. Don\u2019t fear them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 14:10"}, "But all the congregation threatened to stone them with stones.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD\u2019s glory appeared in the Tent of Meeting to all the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 14:11"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cHow long will this people despise me? and how long will they not believe in me, for all the signs\nwhich I have worked amongst them? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 14:12"}, "I will strike them with the pestilence, and disinherit them, and will make of you a nation greater and mightier than\nthey.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 14:13"}, "Musa said to the LORD, \u201cThen the Egyptians will hear it; for you brought up this people in your might from amongst them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 14:14"}, "They will tell it to the inhabitants of this land. They have heard that you LORD are amongst this people; for you LORD\nare seen face to face, and your cloud stands over them, and you go before them, in a pillar of cloud by day, and in a pillar of\nfire by night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 14:15"}, "Now if you killed this people as one man, then the nations which have heard the fame of you will speak, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 14:16"}, "\u2018Because the LORD was not able to bring this people into the land which he swore to them, therefore he has slain them in\nthe wilderness.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 14:17"}, "Now please let the power of the Lord", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is\n\u201cAdonai.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " be great, according as you have spoken, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 14:18"}, "\u2018The LORD is slow to anger, and abundant in loving kindness, forgiving iniquity and disobedience; and he will by no means\nclear the guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children, on the third and on the fourth generation.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 14:19"}, "Please pardon the iniquity of this people according to the greatness of your loving kindness, and just as you have\nforgiven this people, from Egypt even until now.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 14:20"}, "The LORD said, \u201cI have pardoned according to your word; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 14:21"}, "but in very deed\u2014as I live, and as all the earth shall be filled with the LORD\u2019s glory\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 14:22"}, "because all those men who have seen my glory, and my signs, which I worked in Egypt and in the wilderness, yet have\ntempted me these ten times, and have not listened to my voice; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 14:23"}, "surely they shall not see the land which I swore to their fathers, neither shall any of those who despised me see it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 14:24"}, "But my servant Caleb, because he had another spirit with him, and has followed me fully, him I will bring into the land\ninto which he went. His offspring shall possess it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 14:25"}, "Since the Amalekite and the Canaanite dwell in the valley, tomorrow turn and go into the wilderness by the way to the Red\nSea.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 14:26"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and to Harun, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 14:27"}, "\u201cHow long shall I bear with this evil congregation that complain against me? I have heard the complaints of the children\nof Israel, which they complain against me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 14:28"}, "Tell them, \u2018As I live, says the LORD, surely as you have spoken in my ears, so I will do to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 14:29"}, "Your dead bodies shall fall in this wilderness; and all who were counted of you, according to your whole number, from\ntwenty years old and upward, who have complained against me, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 14:30"}, "surely you shall not come into the land concerning which I swore that I would make you dwell therein, except Caleb the\nson of Jephunneh, and Joshua the son of Nun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 14:31"}, "But I will bring your little ones that you said should be captured or killed in, and they shall know the land which you\nhave rejected. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 14:32"}, "But as for you, your dead bodies shall fall in this wilderness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 14:33"}, "Your children shall be wanderers in the wilderness forty years, and shall bear your prostitution, until your dead bodies\nare consumed in the wilderness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 14:34"}, "After the number of the days in which you spied out the land, even forty days, for every day a year, you will bear your\niniquities, even forty years, and you will know my alienation.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 14:35"}, "I, the LORD, have spoken. I will surely do this to all this evil congregation who are gathered together against me. In\nthis wilderness they shall be consumed, and there they shall die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 14:36"}, "The men whom Musa sent to spy out the land, who returned and made all the congregation to murmur against him by bringing\nup an evil report against the land, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 14:37"}, "even those men who brought up an evil report of the land, died by the plague before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 14:38"}, "But Joshua the son of Nun and Caleb the son of Jephunneh remained alive of those men who went to spy out the land.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 14:39"}, "Musa told these words to all the children of Israel, and the people mourned greatly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 14:40"}, "They rose up early in the morning and went up to the top of the mountain, saying, \u201cBehold, we are here, and will go up to\nthe place which the LORD has promised; for we have sinned.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 14:41"}, "Musa said, \u201cWhy now do you disobey the commandment of the LORD, since it shall not prosper?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 14:42"}, "Don\u2019t go up, for the LORD isn\u2019t amongst you; that way you won\u2019t be struck down before your enemies.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 14:43"}, "For there the Amalekite and the Canaanite are before you, and you will fall by the sword because you turned back from\nfollowing the LORD; therefore the LORD will not be with you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 14:44"}, "But they presumed to go up to the top of the mountain. Nevertheless, the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant and Musa didn\u2019t\ndepart out of the camp. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 14:45"}, "Then the Amalekites came down, and the Canaanites who lived in that mountain, and struck them and beat them down, even to\nHormah. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 15:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 15:2"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and tell them, \u2018When you have come into the land of your habitations, which I give to\nyou, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 15:3"}, "and will make an offering by fire to the LORD\u2014a burnt offering, or a sacrifice, to accomplish a vow, or as a free will\noffering, or in your set feasts, to make a pleasant aroma to the LORD, of the herd, or of the flock\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 15:4"}, "then he who offers his offering shall offer to the LORD a meal offering of one tenth of an\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine flour mixed with one fourth of a hin", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:4\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A hin is about 6.5 litres or 1.7 gallons."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of oil. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 15:5"}, "You shall prepare wine for the drink offering, one fourth of a hin, with the burnt offering or for the sacrifice, for each\nlamb. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 15:6"}, "\u201c\u2018For a ram, you shall prepare for a meal offering two tenths of an\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine flour mixed with the third part of a hin of oil;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 15:7"}, "and for the drink offering you shall offer the third part of a hin of wine, of a pleasant aroma to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 15:8"}, "When you prepare a bull for a burnt offering or for a sacrifice, to accomplish a vow, or for peace offerings to the LORD,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 15:9"}, "then he shall offer with the bull a meal offering of three tenths of an\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine flour mixed with half a hin of oil; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 15:10"}, "and you shall offer for the drink offering half a hin of wine, for an offering made by fire, of a pleasant aroma to the\nLORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 15:11"}, "Thus it shall be done for each bull, for each ram, for each of the male lambs, or of the young goats.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 15:12"}, "According to the number that you shall prepare, so you shall do to everyone according to their number.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 15:13"}, "\u201c\u2018All who are native-born shall do these things in this way, in offering an offering made by fire, of a pleasant aroma to\nthe LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 15:14"}, "If a stranger lives as a foreigner with you, or whoever may be amongst you throughout your generations, and will offer an\noffering made by fire, of a pleasant aroma to the LORD, as you do, so he shall do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 15:15"}, "For the assembly, there shall be one statute for you and for the stranger who lives as a foreigner, a statute forever\nthroughout your generations. As you are, so the foreigner shall be before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 15:16"}, "One law and one ordinance shall be for you and for the stranger who lives as a foreigner with you.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 15:17"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 15:18"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and tell them, \u2018When you come into the land where I bring you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 15:19"}, "then it shall be that when you eat of the bread of the land, you shall offer up a wave offering to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 15:20"}, "Of the first of your dough you shall offer up a cake for a wave offering. As the wave offering of the threshing floor, so\nyou shall heave it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 15:21"}, "Of the first of your dough, you shall give to the LORD a wave offering throughout your generations.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 15:22"}, "\u201c\u2018When you err, and don\u2019t observe all these commandments which the LORD has spoken to Musa\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 15:23"}, "even all that the LORD has commanded you by Musa, from the day that the LORD gave commandment and onward throughout your\ngenerations\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 15:24"}, "then it shall be, if it was done unwittingly, without the knowledge of the congregation, that all the congregation shall\noffer one young bull for a burnt offering, for a pleasant aroma to the LORD, with its meal offering and its drink offering,\naccording to the ordinance, and one male goat for a sin offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 15:25"}, "The priest shall make atonement for all the congregation of the children of Israel, and they shall be forgiven; for it\nwas an error, and they have brought their offering, an offering made by fire to the LORD, and their sin offering before the\nLORD, for their error. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 15:26"}, "All the congregation of the children of Israel shall be forgiven, as well as the stranger who lives as a foreigner\namongst them; for with regard to all the people, it was done unwittingly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 15:27"}, "\u201c\u2018If a person sins unwittingly, then he shall offer a female goat a year old for a sin offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 15:28"}, "The priest shall make atonement for the soul who errs when he sins unwittingly before the LORD. He shall make atonement\nfor him; and he shall be forgiven. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 15:29"}, "You shall have one law for him who does anything unwittingly, for him who is native-born amongst the children of Israel,\nand for the stranger who lives as a foreigner amongst them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 15:30"}, "\u201c\u2018But the soul who does anything with a high hand, whether he is native-born or a foreigner, blasphemes the LORD. That\nsoul shall be cut off from amongst his people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 15:31"}, "Because he has despised the LORD\u2019s word, and has broken his commandment, that soul shall be utterly cut off. His iniquity\nshall be on him.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 15:32"}, "While the children of Israel were in the wilderness, they found a man gathering sticks on the Sabbath day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 15:33"}, "Those who found him gathering sticks brought him to Musa and Harun, and to all the congregation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 15:34"}, "They put him in custody, because it had not been declared what should be done to him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 15:35"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cThe man shall surely be put to death. All the congregation shall stone him with stones outside of\nthe camp.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 15:36"}, "All the congregation brought him outside of the camp, and stoned him to death with stones, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 15:37"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 15:38"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and tell them that they should make themselves\nfringes", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:38 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassels (Hebrew \u05e6\u05b4\u05d9\u05e6\u05b4\u059b\u05ea)"]}], "caller": "+"}, " on the borders of their garments throughout their generations, and\nthat they put on the fringe ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:38 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of each border a cord of blue.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 15:39"}, "It shall be to you for a fringe,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:39 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " that you may see it, and remember all the LORD\u2019s\ncommandments, and do them; and that you don\u2019t follow your own heart and your own eyes, after which you used to play the\nprostitute; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 15:40"}, "so that you may remember and do all my commandments, and be holy to your Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 15:41"}, "I am Allah your LORD, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your Allah: I am Allah your LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 16:1"}, "Now Korah, the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, with Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, and On, the\nson of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took some men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 16:2"}, "They rose up before Musa, with some of the children of Israel, two hundred and fifty princes of the congregation, called\nto the assembly, men of renown. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 16:3"}, "They assembled themselves together against Musa and against Harun, and said to them, \u201cYou take too much on yourself, since\nall the congregation are holy, everyone of them, and the LORD is amongst them! Why do you lift yourselves up above the LORD\u2019s\nassembly?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 16:4"}, "When Musa heard it, he fell on his face. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 16:5"}, "He said to Korah and to all his company, \u201cIn the morning, the LORD will show who are his, and who is holy, and will cause\nhim to come near to him. Even him whom he shall choose, he will cause to come near to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 16:6"}, "Do this: have Korah and all his company take censers, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 16:7"}, "put fire in them, and put incense on them before the LORD tomorrow. It shall be that the man whom the LORD chooses, he\nshall be holy. You have gone too far, you sons of Levi!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 16:8"}, "Musa said to Korah, \u201cHear now, you sons of Levi! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 16:9"}, "Is it a small thing to you that Allah of Israel has separated you from the congregation of Israel, to bring you near to\nhimself, to do the service of the LORD\u2019s tabernacle, and to stand before the congregation to minister to them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 16:10"}, "and that he has brought you near, and all your brothers the sons of Levi with you? Do you seek the priesthood also?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 16:11"}, "Therefore you and all your company have gathered together against the LORD! What is Harun that you complain against him?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 16:12"}, "Musa sent to call Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab; and they said, \u201cWe won\u2019t come up!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 16:13"}, "Is it a small thing that you have brought us up out of a land flowing with milk and honey, to kill us in the wilderness,\nbut you must also make yourself a prince over us? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 16:14"}, "Moreover you haven\u2019t brought us into a land flowing with milk and honey, nor given us inheritance of fields and\nvineyards. Will you put out the eyes of these men? We won\u2019t come up.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 16:15"}, "Musa was very angry, and said to the LORD, \u201cDon\u2019t respect their offering. I have not taken one donkey from them, neither\nhave I hurt one of them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 16:16"}, "Musa said to Korah, \u201cYou and all your company go before the LORD, you, and they, and Harun, tomorrow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 16:17"}, "Each man take his censer and put incense on it, and each man bring before the LORD his censer, two hundred and fifty\ncensers; you also, and Harun, each with his censer.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 16:18"}, "They each took his censer, and put fire in it, and laid incense on it, and stood at the door of the Tent of Meeting with\nMusa and Harun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 16:19"}, "Korah assembled all the congregation opposite them to the door of the Tent of Meeting.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD\u2019s glory appeared to all the congregation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 16:20"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and to Harun, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 16:21"}, "\u201cSeparate yourselves from amongst this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 16:22"}, "They fell on their faces, and said, \u201cAllah, Allah of the spirits of all flesh, shall one man sin, and will you be angry\nwith all the congregation?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 16:23"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 16:24"}, "\u201cSpeak to the congregation, saying, \u2018Get away from around the tent of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram!\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 16:25"}, "Musa rose up and went to Dathan and Abiram; and the elders of Israel followed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 16:26"}, "He spoke to the congregation, saying, \u201cDepart, please, from the tents of these wicked men, and touch nothing of theirs,\nlest you be consumed in all their sins!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 16:27"}, "So they went away from the tent of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram, on every side. Dathan and Abiram came out, and stood at the\ndoor of their tents with their wives, their sons, and their little ones.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 16:28"}, "Musa said, \u201cHereby you shall know that the LORD has sent me to do all these works; for they are not from my own mind.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 16:29"}, "If these men die the common death of all men, or if they experience what all men experience, then the LORD hasn\u2019t sent\nme. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 16:30"}, "But if the LORD makes a new thing, and the ground opens its mouth, and swallows them up with all that belong to them, and\nthey go down alive into Sheol,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " then you shall understand that these men have despised the LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 16:31"}, "As he finished speaking all these words, the ground that was under them split apart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 16:32"}, "The earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up with their households, all of Korah\u2019s men, and all their goods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 16:33"}, "So they, and all that belonged to them went down alive into Sheol.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " The earth closed on them, and they perished from amongst the assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 16:34"}, "All Israel that were around them fled at their cry; for they said, \u201cLest the earth swallow us up!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 16:35"}, "Fire came out from the LORD, and devoured the two hundred and fifty men who offered the incense.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 16:36"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 16:37"}, "\u201cSpeak to Eleazar the son of Harun the priest, that he take up the censers out of the burning, and scatter the fire away\nfrom the camp; for they are holy, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 16:38"}, "even the censers of those who sinned against their own lives. Let them be beaten into plates for a covering of the altar,\nfor they offered them before the LORD. Therefore they are holy. They shall be a sign to the children of Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 16:39"}, "Eleazar the priest took the bronze censers which those who were burnt had offered; and they beat them out for a covering\nof the altar, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 16:40"}, "to be a memorial to the children of Israel, to the end that no stranger who isn\u2019t of the offspring of Harun, would come\nnear to burn incense before the LORD, that he not be as Korah, and as his company; as the LORD spoke to him by Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 16:41"}, "But on the next day all the congregation of the children of Israel complained against Musa and against Harun, saying,\n\u201cYou have killed the LORD\u2019s people!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 16:42"}, "When the congregation was assembled against Musa and against Harun, they looked towards the Tent of Meeting. Behold, the\ncloud covered it, and the LORD\u2019s glory appeared. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 16:43"}, "Musa and Harun came to the front of the Tent of Meeting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 16:44"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 16:45"}, "\u201cGet away from amongst this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment!\u201d They fell on their faces.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 16:46"}, "Musa said to Harun, \u201cTake your censer, put fire from the altar in it, lay incense on it, carry it quickly to the\ncongregation, and make atonement for them; for wrath has gone out from the LORD! The plague has begun.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 16:47"}, "Harun did as Musa said, and ran into the middle of the assembly. The plague had already begun amongst the people. He put\non the incense, and made atonement for the people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 16:48"}, "He stood between the dead and the living; and the plague was stayed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 16:49"}, "Now those who died by the plague were fourteen thousand and seven hundred, in addition to those who died about the matter\nof Korah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 16:50"}, "Harun returned to Musa to the door of the Tent of Meeting, and the plague was stopped.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 17:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 17:2"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and take rods from them, one for each fathers\u2019 house, of all their princes according to\ntheir fathers\u2019 houses, twelve rods. Write each man\u2019s name on his rod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 17:3"}, "You shall write Harun\u2019s name on Levi\u2019s rod. There shall be one rod for each head of their fathers\u2019 houses.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 17:4"}, "You shall lay them up in the Tent of Meeting before the covenant, where I meet with you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 17:5"}, "It shall happen that the rod of the man whom I shall choose shall bud. I will make the murmurings of the children of\nIsrael, which they murmur against you, cease from me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 17:6"}, "Musa spoke to the children of Israel; and all their princes gave him rods, for each prince one, according to their\nfathers\u2019 houses, a total of twelve rods. Harun\u2019s rod was amongst their rods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 17:7"}, "Musa laid up the rods before the LORD in the Tent of the Testimony.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 17:8"}, "On the next day, Musa went into the Tent of the Testimony; and behold, Harun\u2019s rod for the house of Levi had sprouted,\nbudded, produced blossoms, and bore ripe almonds. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 17:9"}, "Musa brought out all the rods from before the LORD to all the children of Israel. They looked, and each man took his rod.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 17:10"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cPut back the rod of Harun before the covenant, to be kept for a token against the children of\nrebellion; that you may make an end of their complaining against me, that they not die.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 17:11"}, "Musa did so. As the LORD commanded him, so he did. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 17:12"}, "The children of Israel spoke to Musa, saying, \u201cBehold, we perish! We are undone! We are all undone!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 17:13"}, "Everyone who keeps approaching the LORD\u2019s tabernacle, dies! Will we all perish?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 18:1"}, "The LORD said to Harun, \u201cYou and your sons and your fathers\u2019 house with you shall bear the iniquity of the sanctuary; and\nyou and your sons with you shall bear the iniquity of your priesthood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 18:2"}, "Bring your brothers also, the tribe of Levi, the tribe of your father, near with you, that they may be joined to you, and\nminister to you; but you and your sons with you shall be before the Tent of the Testimony.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 18:3"}, "They shall keep your commands and the duty of the whole Tent; only they shall not come near to the vessels of the\nsanctuary and to the altar, that they not die, neither they nor you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 18:4"}, "They shall be joined to you and keep the responsibility of the Tent of Meeting, for all the service of the Tent. A\nstranger shall not come near to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 18:5"}, "\u201cYou shall perform the duty of the sanctuary and the duty of the altar, that there be no more wrath on the children of\nIsrael. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 18:6"}, "Behold, I myself have taken your brothers the Levites from amongst the children of Israel. They are a gift to you,\ndedicated to the LORD, to do the service of the Tent of Meeting.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 18:7"}, "You and your sons with you shall keep your priesthood for everything of the altar, and for that within the veil. You shall\nserve. I give you the service of the priesthood as a gift. The stranger who comes near shall be put to death.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 18:8"}, "The LORD spoke to Harun, \u201cBehold, I myself have given you the command of my wave offerings, even all the holy things of\nthe children of Israel. I have given them to you by reason of the anointing, and to your sons, as a portion forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 18:9"}, "This shall be yours of the most holy things from the fire: every offering of theirs, even every meal offering of theirs,\nand every sin offering of theirs, and every trespass offering of theirs, which they shall render to me, shall be most holy for\nyou and for your sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 18:10"}, "You shall eat of it like the most holy things. Every male shall eat of it. It shall be holy to you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 18:11"}, "\u201cThis is yours, too: the wave offering of their gift, even all the wave offerings of the children of Israel. I have given\nthem to you, and to your sons and to your daughters with you, as a portion forever. Everyone who is clean in your house shall\neat of it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 18:12"}, "\u201cI have given to you all the best of the oil, all the best of the vintage, and of the grain, the first fruits of them\nwhich they give to the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 18:13"}, "The first-ripe fruits of all that is in their land, which they bring to the LORD, shall be yours. Everyone who is clean\nin your house shall eat of it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 18:14"}, "\u201cEverything devoted in Israel shall be yours. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 18:15"}, "Everything that opens the womb, of all flesh which they offer to the LORD, both of man and animal, shall be yours.\nNevertheless, you shall surely redeem the firstborn of man, and you shall redeem the firstborn of unclean animals.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 18:16"}, "You shall redeem those who are to be redeemed of them from a month old, according to your estimation, for five shekels of\nmoney, according to the shekel", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of the sanctuary, which weighs twenty gerahs.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:16\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A gerah is about 0.5 grams or about 7.7 grains."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 18:17"}, "\u201cBut you shall not redeem the firstborn of a cow, or the firstborn of a sheep, or the firstborn of a goat. They are holy.\nYou shall sprinkle their blood on the altar, and shall burn their fat for an offering made by fire, for a pleasant aroma to the\nLORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 18:18"}, "Their meat shall be yours, as the wave offering breast and as the right thigh, it shall be yours.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 18:19"}, "All the wave offerings of the holy things which the children of Israel offer to the LORD, I have given you and your sons\nand your daughters with you, as a portion forever. It is a covenant of salt forever before the LORD to you and to your\noffspring with you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 18:20"}, "The LORD said to Harun, \u201cYou shall have no inheritance in their land, neither shall you have any portion amongst them. I\nam your portion and your inheritance amongst the children of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 18:21"}, "\u201cTo the children of Levi, behold, I have given all the tithe in Israel for an inheritance, in return for their service\nwhich they serve, even the service of the Tent of Meeting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 18:22"}, "Henceforth the children of Israel shall not come near the Tent of Meeting, lest they bear sin, and die.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 18:23"}, "But the Levites shall do the service of the Tent of Meeting, and they shall bear their iniquity. It shall be a statute\nforever throughout your generations. Amongst the children of Israel, they shall have no inheritance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 18:24"}, "For the tithe of the children of Israel, which they offer as a wave offering to the LORD, I have given to the Levites for\nan inheritance. Therefore I have said to them, \u2018Amongst the children of Israel they shall have no inheritance.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 18:25"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 18:26"}, "\u201cMoreover you shall speak to the Levites, and tell them, \u2018When you take of the children of Israel the tithe which I have\ngiven you from them for your inheritance, then you shall offer up a wave offering of it for the LORD, a tithe of the tithe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 18:27"}, "Your wave offering shall be credited to you, as though it were the grain of the threshing floor, and as the fullness of\nthe wine press. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 18:28"}, "Thus you also shall offer a wave offering to the LORD of all your tithes, which you receive of the children of Israel;\nand of it you shall give the LORD\u2019s wave offering to Harun the priest.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 18:29"}, "Out of all your gifts, you shall offer every wave offering to the LORD, of all its best parts, even the holy part of it.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 18:30"}, "\u201cTherefore you shall tell them, \u2018When you heave its best from it, then it shall be credited to the Levites as the\nincrease of the threshing floor, and as the increase of the wine press.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 18:31"}, "You may eat it anywhere, you and your households, for it is your reward in return for your service in the Tent of\nMeeting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 18:32"}, "You shall bear no sin by reason of it, when you have heaved from it its best. You shall not profane the holy things of\nthe children of Israel, that you not die.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 19:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and to Harun, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 19:2"}, "\u201cThis is the statute of the law which the LORD has commanded. Tell the children of Israel to bring you a red heifer\nwithout spot, in which is no defect, and which was never yoked. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 19:3"}, "You shall give her to Eleazar the priest, and he shall bring her outside of the camp, and one shall kill her before his\nface. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 19:4"}, "Eleazar the priest shall take some of her blood with his finger, and sprinkle her blood towards the front of the Tent of\nMeeting seven times. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 19:5"}, "One shall burn the heifer in his sight; her skin, and her meat, and her blood, with her dung, shall he burn.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 19:6"}, "The priest shall take cedar wood, hyssop, and scarlet, and cast it into the middle of the burning of the heifer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 19:7"}, "Then the priest shall wash his clothes, and he shall bathe his flesh in water, and afterward he shall come into the camp,\nand the priest shall be unclean until the evening. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 19:8"}, "He who burns her shall wash his clothes in water, and bathe his flesh in water, and shall be unclean until the evening.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 19:9"}, "\u201cA man who is clean shall gather up the ashes of the heifer, and lay them up outside of the camp in a clean place; and it\nshall be kept for the congregation of the children of Israel for use in water for cleansing impurity. It is a sin offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 19:10"}, "He who gathers the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes, and be unclean until the evening. It shall be to the\nchildren of Israel, and to the stranger who lives as a foreigner amongst them, for a statute forever.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 19:11"}, "\u201cHe who touches the dead body of any man shall be unclean seven days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 19:12"}, "He shall purify himself with water on the third day, and on the seventh day he shall be clean; but if he doesn\u2019t purify\nhimself the third day, then the seventh day he shall not be clean.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 19:13"}, "Whoever touches a dead person, the body of a man who has died, and doesn\u2019t purify himself, defiles the LORD\u2019s tabernacle;\nand that soul shall be cut off from Israel; because the water for impurity was not sprinkled on him, he shall be unclean. His\nuncleanness is yet on him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 19:14"}, "\u201cThis is the law when a man dies in a tent: everyone who comes into the tent, and everyone who is in the tent, shall be\nunclean seven days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 19:15"}, "Every open vessel, which has no covering bound on it, is unclean.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 19:16"}, "\u201cWhoever in the open field touches one who is slain with a sword, or a dead body, or a bone of a man, or a grave, shall\nbe unclean seven days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 19:17"}, "\u201cFor the unclean, they shall take of the ashes of the burning of the sin offering; and running water shall be poured on\nthem in a vessel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 19:18"}, "A clean person shall take hyssop, dip it in the water, and sprinkle it on the tent, on all the vessels, on the persons\nwho were there, and on him who touched the bone, or the slain, or the dead, or the grave.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 19:19"}, "The clean person shall sprinkle on the unclean on the third day, and on the seventh day. On the seventh day, he shall\npurify him. He shall wash his clothes and bathe himself in water, and shall be clean at evening.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 19:20"}, "But the man who shall be unclean, and shall not purify himself, that soul shall be cut off from amongst the assembly,\nbecause he has defiled the sanctuary of the LORD. The water for impurity has not been sprinkled on him. He is unclean.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 19:21"}, "It shall be a perpetual statute to them. He who sprinkles the water for impurity shall wash his clothes, and he who\ntouches the water for impurity shall be unclean until evening. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 19:22"}, "\u201cWhatever the unclean person touches shall be unclean; and the soul that touches it shall be unclean until evening.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 20:1"}, "The children of Israel, even the whole congregation, came into the wilderness of Zin in the first month. The people stayed\nin Kadesh. Miriam died there, and was buried there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 20:2"}, "There was no water for the congregation; and they assembled themselves together against Musa and against Harun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 20:3"}, "The people quarrelled with Musa, and spoke, saying, \u201cWe wish that we had died when our brothers died before the LORD!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 20:4"}, "Why have you brought the LORD\u2019s assembly into this wilderness, that we should die there, we and our animals?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 20:5"}, "Why have you made us to come up out of Egypt, to bring us in to this evil place? It is no place of seed, or of figs, or of\nvines, or of pomegranates; neither is there any water to drink.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 20:6"}, "Musa and Harun went from the presence of the assembly to the door of the Tent of Meeting, and fell on their faces. The\nLORD\u2019s glory appeared to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 20:7"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 20:8"}, "\u201cTake the rod, and assemble the congregation, you, and Harun your brother, and speak to the rock before their eyes, that\nit pour out its water. You shall bring water to them out of the rock; so you shall give the congregation and their livestock\ndrink.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 20:9"}, "Musa took the rod from before the LORD, as he commanded him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 20:10"}, "Musa and Harun gathered the assembly together before the rock, and he said to them, \u201cHear now, you rebels! Shall we bring\nwater out of this rock for you?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 20:11"}, "Musa lifted up his hand, and struck the rock with his rod twice, and water came out abundantly. The congregation and\ntheir livestock drank. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 20:12"}, "The LORD said to Musa and Harun, \u201cBecause you didn\u2019t believe in me, to sanctify me in the eyes of the children of Israel,\ntherefore you shall not bring this assembly into the land which I have given them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 20:13"}, "These are the waters of Meribah;", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["20:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cMeribah\u201d means\n\u201cquarrelling\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " because the children of Israel strove with the LORD, and he was sanctified in them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 20:14"}, "Musa sent messengers from Kadesh to the king of Edom, saying:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cYour brother Israel says: You know all the travail that has happened to us;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 20:15"}, "how our fathers went down into Egypt, and we lived in Egypt a long time. The Egyptians mistreated us and our fathers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 20:16"}, "When we cried to the LORD, he heard our voice, sent an angel, and brought us out of Egypt. Behold, we are in Kadesh, a\ncity in the edge of your border. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 20:17"}, "\u201cPlease let us pass through your land. We will not pass through field or through vineyard, neither will we drink from the\nwater of the wells. We will go along the king\u2019s highway. We will not turn away to the right hand nor to the left, until we have\npassed your border.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 20:18"}, "Edom said to him, \u201cYou shall not pass through me, lest I come out with the sword against you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 20:19"}, "The children of Israel said to him, \u201cWe will go up by the highway; and if we drink your water, I and my livestock, then I\nwill give its price. Only let me, without doing anything else, pass through on my feet.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 20:20"}, "He said, \u201cYou shall not pass through.\u201d Edom came out against him with many people, and with a strong hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 20:21"}, "Thus Edom refused to give Israel passage through his border, so Israel turned away from him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 20:22"}, "They travelled from Kadesh, and the children of Israel, even the whole congregation, came to Mount Hor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 20:23"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa and Harun in Mount Hor, by the border of the land of Edom, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 20:24"}, "\u201cHarun shall be gathered to his people; for he shall not enter into the land which I have given to the children of\nIsrael, because you rebelled against my word at the waters of Meribah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 20:25"}, "Take Harun and Eleazar his son, and bring them up to Mount Hor;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 20:26"}, "and strip Harun of his garments, and put them on Eleazar his son. Harun shall be gathered, and shall die there.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 20:27"}, "Musa did as the LORD commanded. They went up onto Mount Hor in the sight of all the congregation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 20:28"}, "Musa stripped Harun of his garments, and put them on Eleazar his son. Harun died there on the top of the mountain, and\nMusa and Eleazar came down from the mountain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 20:29"}, "When all the congregation saw that Harun was dead, they wept for Harun thirty days, even all the house of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 21:1"}, "The Canaanite, the king of Arad, who lived in the South, heard that Israel came by the way of Atharim. He fought against\nIsrael, and took some of them captive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 21:2"}, "Israel vowed a vow to the LORD, and said, \u201cIf you will indeed deliver this people into my hand, then I will utterly\ndestroy their cities.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 21:3"}, "The LORD listened to the voice of Israel, and delivered up the Canaanites; and they utterly destroyed them and their\ncities. The name of the place was called Hormah.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["21:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cHormah\u201d means\n\u201cdestruction\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 21:4"}, "They travelled from Mount Hor by the way to the Red Sea, to go around the land of Edom. The soul of the people was very\ndiscouraged because of the journey. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 21:5"}, "The people spoke against Allah and against Musa: \u201cWhy have you brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? For\nthere is no bread, there is no water, and our soul loathes this disgusting food!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 21:6"}, "The LORD sent venomous snakes amongst the people, and they bit the people. Many people of Israel died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 21:7"}, "The people came to Musa, and said, \u201cWe have sinned, because we have spoken against the LORD and against you. Pray to the\nLORD, that he take away the serpents from us.\u201d Musa prayed for the people.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 21:8"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cMake a venomous snake, and set it on a pole. It shall happen that everyone who is bitten, when he\nsees it, shall live.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 21:9"}, "Musa made a serpent of bronze, and set it on the pole. If a serpent had bitten any man, when he looked at the serpent of\nbronze, he lived. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 21:10"}, "The children of Israel travelled, and encamped in Oboth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 21:11"}, "They travelled from Oboth, and encamped at Iyeabarim, in the wilderness which is before Moab, towards the sunrise.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 21:12"}, "From there they travelled, and encamped in the valley of Zered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 21:13"}, "From there they travelled, and encamped on the other side of the Arnon, which is in the wilderness that comes out of the\nborder of the Amorites; for the Arnon is the border of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 21:14"}, "Therefore it is said in the book of the Wars of the LORD, \u201cVaheb in Suphah, the valleys of the Arnon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 21:15"}, "the slope of the valleys that incline towards the dwelling of Ar, leans on the border of Moab.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 21:16"}, "From there they travelled to Beer; that is the well of which the LORD said to Musa, \u201cGather the people together, and I\nwill give them water.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 21:17"}, "Then Israel sang this song: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cSpring up, well! Sing to it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 21:18"}, "the well, which the princes dug, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which the nobles of the people dug, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with the sceptre, and with their poles.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["From the wilderness they travelled to Mattanah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 21:19"}, "and from Mattanah to Nahaliel; and from Nahaliel to Bamoth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 21:20"}, "and from Bamoth to the valley that is in the field of Moab, to the top of Pisgah, which looks down on the desert.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 21:21"}, "Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 21:22"}, "\u201cLet me pass through your land. We will not turn away into field or vineyard. We will not drink of the water of the\nwells. We will go by the king\u2019s highway, until we have passed your border.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 21:23"}, "Sihon would not allow Israel to pass through his border, but Sihon gathered all his people together, and went out against\nIsrael into the wilderness, and came to Jahaz. He fought against Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 21:24"}, "Israel struck him with the edge of the sword, and possessed his land from the Arnon to the Jabbok, even to the children\nof Ammon; for the border of the children of Ammon was fortified.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 21:25"}, "Israel took all these cities. Israel lived in all the cities of the Amorites, in Heshbon, and in all its villages.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 21:26"}, "For Heshbon was the city of Sihon the king of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab, and taken all\nhis land out of his hand, even to the Arnon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 21:27"}, "Therefore those who speak in proverbs say, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cCome to Heshbon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let the city of Sihon be built and established; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 21:28"}, "for a fire has gone out of Heshbon, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a flame from the city of Sihon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["It has devoured Ar of Moab, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The lords of the high places of the Arnon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 21:29"}, "Woe to you, Moab! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You are undone, people of Chemosh! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He has given his sons as fugitives, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his daughters into captivity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to Sihon king of the Amorites. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 21:30"}, "We have shot at them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Heshbon has perished even to Dibon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["We have laid waste even to Nophah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Which reaches to Medeba.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 21:31"}, "Thus Israel lived in the land of the Amorites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 21:32"}, "Musa sent to spy out Jazer. They took its villages, and drove out the Amorites who were there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 21:33"}, "They turned and went up by the way of Bashan. Og the king of Bashan went out against them, he and all his people, to\nbattle at Edrei. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 21:34"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cDon\u2019t fear him, for I have delivered him into your hand, with all his people, and his land. You\nshall do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 21:35"}, "So they struck him, with his sons and all his people, until there were no survivors; and they possessed his land.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 22:1"}, "The children of Israel travelled, and encamped in the plains of Moab beyond the Jordan at Jericho.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 22:2"}, "Balak the son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 22:3"}, "Moab was very afraid of the people, because they were many. Moab was distressed because of the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 22:4"}, "Moab said to the elders of Midian, \u201cNow this multitude will lick up all that is around us, as the ox licks up the grass of\nthe field.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Balak the son of Zippor was king of Moab at that time. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 22:5"}, "He sent messengers to Balaam the son of Beor, to Pethor, which is by the River, to the land of the children of his people,\nto call him, saying, \u201cBehold, there is a people who came out of Egypt. Behold, they cover the surface of the earth, and they\nare staying opposite me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 22:6"}, "Please come now therefore, and curse this people for me; for they are too mighty for me. Perhaps I shall prevail, that we\nmay strike them, and that I may drive them out of the land; for I know that he whom you bless is blessed, and he whom you curse\nis cursed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 22:7"}, "The elders of Moab and the elders of Midian departed with the rewards of divination in their hand. They came to Balaam,\nand spoke to him the words of Balak. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 22:8"}, "He said to them, \u201cLodge here this night, and I will bring you word again, as the LORD shall speak to me.\u201d The princes of\nMoab stayed with Balaam. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 22:9"}, "Allah came to Balaam, and said, \u201cWho are these men with you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 22:10"}, "Balaam said to Allah, \u201cBalak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, has said to me,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 22:11"}, "\u2018Behold, the people that has come out of Egypt covers the surface of the earth. Now, come curse me them. Perhaps I shall\nbe able to fight against them, and shall drive them out.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 22:12"}, "Allah said to Balaam, \u201cYou shall not go with them. You shall not curse the people, for they are blessed.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 22:13"}, "Balaam rose up in the morning, and said to the princes of Balak, \u201cGo to your land; for the LORD refuses to permit me to\ngo with you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 22:14"}, "The princes of Moab rose up, and they went to Balak, and said, \u201cBalaam refuses to come with us.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 22:15"}, "Balak again sent princes, more, and more honourable than they.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 22:16"}, "They came to Balaam, and said to him, \u201cBalak the son of Zippor says, \u2018Please let nothing hinder you from coming to me,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 22:17"}, "for I will promote you to very great honour, and whatever you say to me I will do. Please come therefore, and curse this\npeople for me.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 22:18"}, "Balaam answered the servants of Balak, \u201cIf Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I can\u2019t go beyond the\nword of the LORD my Allah, to do less or more. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 22:19"}, "Now therefore please stay here tonight as well, that I may know what else the LORD will speak to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 22:20"}, "Allah came to Balaam at night, and said to him, \u201cIf the men have come to call you, rise up, go with them; but only the\nword which I speak to you, that you shall do.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 22:21"}, "Balaam rose up in the morning, and saddled his donkey, and went with the princes of Moab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 22:22"}, "Allah\u2019s anger burnt because he went; and the LORD\u2019s angel placed himself in the way as an adversary against him. Now he\nwas riding on his donkey, and his two servants were with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 22:23"}, "The donkey saw the LORD\u2019s angel standing in the way, with his sword drawn in his hand; and the donkey turned out of the\npath, and went into the field. Balaam struck the donkey, to turn her into the path.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 22:24"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s angel stood in a narrow path between the vineyards, a wall being on this side, and a wall on that side.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 22:25"}, "The donkey saw the LORD\u2019s angel, and she thrust herself to the wall, and crushed Balaam\u2019s foot against the wall. He\nstruck her again. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 22:26"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel went further, and stood in a narrow place, where there was no way to turn either to the right hand or to\nthe left. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 22:27"}, "The donkey saw the LORD\u2019s angel, and she lay down under Balaam. Balaam\u2019s anger burnt, and he struck the donkey with his\nstaff. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 22:28"}, "The LORD opened the mouth of the donkey, and she said to Balaam, \u201cWhat have I done to you, that you have struck me these\nthree times?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 22:29"}, "Balaam said to the donkey, \u201cBecause you have mocked me, I wish there were a sword in my hand, for now I would have killed\nyou.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 22:30"}, "The donkey said to Balaam, \u201cAm I not your donkey, on which you have ridden all your life long until today? Was I ever in\nthe habit of doing so to you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cNo.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 22:31"}, "Then the LORD opened the eyes of Balaam, and he saw the LORD\u2019s angel standing in the way, with his sword drawn in his\nhand; and he bowed his head, and fell on his face. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 22:32"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to him, \u201cWhy have you struck your donkey these three times? Behold, I have come out as an\nadversary, because your way is perverse before me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 22:33"}, "The donkey saw me, and turned away before me these three times. Unless she had turned away from me, surely now I would\nhave killed you, and saved her alive.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 22:34"}, "Balaam said to the LORD\u2019s angel, \u201cI have sinned; for I didn\u2019t know that you stood in the way against me. Now therefore,\nif it displeases you, I will go back again.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 22:35"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to Balaam, \u201cGo with the men; but only the word that I shall speak to you, that you shall speak.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["So Balaam went with the princes of Balak. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 22:36"}, "When Balak heard that Balaam had come, he went out to meet him to the City of Moab, which is on the border of the Arnon,\nwhich is in the utmost part of the border. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 22:37"}, "Balak said to Balaam, \u201cDidn\u2019t I earnestly send for you to summon you? Why didn\u2019t you come to me? Am I not able indeed to\npromote you to honour?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 22:38"}, "Balaam said to Balak, \u201cBehold, I have come to you. Have I now any power at all to speak anything? The word that Allah\nputs in my mouth, that shall I speak.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 22:39"}, "Balaam went with Balak, and they came to Kiriath Huzoth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 22:40"}, "Balak sacrificed cattle and sheep, and sent to Balaam, and to the princes who were with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 22:41"}, "In the morning, Balak took Balaam, and brought him up into the high places of Baal; and he saw from there part of the\npeople. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 23:1"}, "Balaam said to Balak, \u201cBuild here seven altars for me, and prepare here seven bulls and seven rams for me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 23:2"}, "Balak did as Balaam had spoken; and Balak and Balaam offered on every altar a bull and a ram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 23:3"}, "Balaam said to Balak, \u201cStand by your burnt offering, and I will go. Perhaps the LORD will come to meet me. Whatever he\nshows me I will tell you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He went to a bare height. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 23:4"}, "Allah met Balaam, and he said to him, \u201cI have prepared the seven altars, and I have offered up a bull and a ram on every\naltar.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 23:5"}, "The LORD put a word in Balaam\u2019s mouth, and said, \u201cReturn to Balak, and thus you shall speak.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 23:6"}, "He returned to him, and behold, he was standing by his burnt offering, he, and all the princes of Moab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 23:7"}, "He took up his parable, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cFrom Aram has Balak brought me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the king of Moab from the mountains of the East. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Come, curse Yaqub for me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Come, defy Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 23:8"}, "How shall I curse whom Allah has not cursed? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["How shall I defy whom the LORD has not defied? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 23:9"}, "For from the top of the rocks I see him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From the hills I see him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, it is a people that dwells alone, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shall not be listed amongst the nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 23:10"}, "Who can count the dust of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or count the fourth part of Israel? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let me die the death of the righteous! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let my last end be like his!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 23:11"}, "Balak said to Balaam, \u201cWhat have you done to me? I took you to curse my enemies, and behold, you have blessed them\naltogether.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 23:12"}, "He answered and said, \u201cMust I not take heed to speak that which the LORD puts in my mouth?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 23:13"}, "Balak said to him, \u201cPlease come with me to another place, where you may see them. You shall see just part of them, and\nshall not see them all. Curse them from there for me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 23:14"}, "He took him into the field of Zophim, to the top of Pisgah, and built seven altars, and offered up a bull and a ram on\nevery altar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 23:15"}, "He said to Balak, \u201cStand here by your burnt offering, while I meet Allah over there.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 23:16"}, "The LORD met Balaam, and put a word in his mouth, and said, \u201cReturn to Balak, and say this.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 23:17"}, "He came to him, and behold, he was standing by his burnt offering, and the princes of Moab with him. Balak said to him,\n\u201cWhat has the LORD spoken?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 23:18"}, "He took up his parable, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cRise up, Balak, and hear! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Listen to me, you son of Zippor. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 23:19"}, "Allah is not a man, that he should lie, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor a son of man, that he should repent. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Has he said, and will he not do it? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Or has he spoken, and will he not make it good? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 23:20"}, "Behold, I have received a command to bless. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has blessed, and I can\u2019t reverse it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 23:21"}, "He has not seen iniquity in Yaqub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Neither has he seen perverseness in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The LORD his Allah is with him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The shout of a king is amongst them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 23:22"}, "Allah brings them out of Egypt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has as it were the strength of the wild ox. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 23:23"}, "Surely there is no enchantment with Yaqub; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Neither is there any divination with Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Now it shall be said of Yaqub and of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018What has Allah done!\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 23:24"}, "Behold, a people rises up as a lioness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["As a lion he lifts himself up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He shall not lie down until he eats of the prey, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and drinks the blood of the slain.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 23:25"}, "Balak said to Balaam, \u201cNeither curse them at all, nor bless them at all.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 23:26"}, "But Balaam answered Balak, \u201cDidn\u2019t I tell you, saying, \u2018All that the LORD speaks, that I must do?\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 23:27"}, "Balak said to Balaam, \u201cCome now, I will take you to another place; perhaps it will please Allah that you may curse them\nfor me from there.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 23:28"}, "Balak took Balaam to the top of Peor, that looks down on the desert.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 23:29"}, "Balaam said to Balak, \u201cBuild seven altars for me here, and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me here.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 23:30"}, "Balak did as Balaam had said, and offered up a bull and a ram on every altar.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 24:1"}, "When Balaam saw that it pleased the LORD to bless Israel, he didn\u2019t go, as at the other times, to use divination, but he\nset his face towards the wilderness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 24:2"}, "Balaam lifted up his eyes, and he saw Israel dwelling according to their tribes; and the Spirit of Allah came on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 24:3"}, "He took up his parable, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBalaam the son of Beor says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the man whose eyes are open says; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 24:4"}, "he says, who hears the words of Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who sees the vision of the Almighty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["falling down, and having his eyes open: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 24:5"}, "How goodly are your tents, Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your dwellings, Israel! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 24:6"}, "As valleys they are spread out, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as gardens by the riverside, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as aloes which the LORD has planted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as cedar trees beside the waters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 24:7"}, "Water shall flow from his buckets. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His seed shall be in many waters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["His king shall be higher than Agag. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His kingdom shall be exalted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 24:8"}, "Allah brings him out of Egypt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has as it were the strength of the wild ox. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He shall consume the nations his adversaries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["shall break their bones in pieces, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and pierce them with his arrows. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 24:9"}, "He couched, he lay down as a lion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as a lioness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who shall rouse him up? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Everyone who blesses you is blessed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Everyone who curses you is cursed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 24:10"}, "Balak\u2019s anger burnt against Balaam, and he struck his hands together. Balak said to Balaam, \u201cI called you to curse my\nenemies, and, behold, you have altogether blessed them these three times.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 24:11"}, "Therefore, flee to your place, now! I thought to promote you to great honour; but, behold, the LORD has kept you back\nfrom honour.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 24:12"}, "Balaam said to Balak, \u201cDidn\u2019t I also tell your messengers whom you sent to me, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 24:13"}, "\u2018If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I can\u2019t go beyond the LORD\u2019s word, to do either good or bad\nfrom my own mind. I will say what the LORD says\u2019? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 24:14"}, "Now, behold, I go to my people. Come, I will inform you what this people shall do to your people in the latter days.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 24:15"}, "He took up his parable, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBalaam the son of Beor says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the man whose eyes are open says; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 24:16"}, "he says, who hears the words of Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["knows the knowledge of the Most High, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and who sees the vision of the Almighty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Falling down, and having his eyes open: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 24:17"}, "I see him, but not now. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I see him, but not near. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["A star will come out of Yaqub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A sceptre will rise out of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and shall strike through the corners of Moab, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and crush all the sons of Sheth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 24:18"}, "Edom shall be a possession. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Seir, his enemies, also shall be a possession, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["while Israel does valiantly. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 24:19"}, "Out of Yaqub shall one have dominion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shall destroy the remnant from the city.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 24:20"}, "He looked at Amalek, and took up his parable, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAmalek was the first of the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["But his latter end shall come to destruction.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 24:21"}, "He looked at the Kenite, and took up his parable, and said,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cYour dwelling place is strong. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your nest is set in the rock. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 24:22"}, "Nevertheless Kain shall be wasted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["until Asshur carries you away captive.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 24:23"}, "He took up his parable, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAlas, who shall live when Allah does this? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 24:24"}, "But ships shall come from the coast of Kittim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They shall afflict Asshur, and shall afflict Eber. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He also shall come to destruction.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 24:25"}, "Balaam rose up, and went and returned to his place; and Balak also went his way.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 25:1"}, "Israel stayed in Shittim; and the people began to play the prostitute with the daughters of Moab;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 25:2"}, "for they called the people to the sacrifices of their gods. The people ate and bowed down to their gods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 25:3"}, "Israel joined himself to Baal Peor, and the LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 25:4"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cTake all the chiefs of the people, and hang them up to the LORD before the sun, that the fierce\nanger of the LORD may turn away from Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 25:5"}, "Musa said to the judges of Israel, \u201cEveryone kill his men who have joined themselves to Baal Peor.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 25:6"}, "Behold, one of the children of Israel came and brought to his brothers a Midianite woman in the sight of Musa, and in the\nsight of all the congregation of the children of Israel, while they were weeping at the door of the Tent of Meeting.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 25:7"}, "When Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Harun the priest, saw it, he rose up from the middle of the congregation,\nand took a spear in his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 25:8"}, "He went after the man of Israel into the pavilion, and thrust both of them through, the man of Israel, and the woman\nthrough her body. So the plague was stopped amongst the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 25:9"}, "Those who died by the plague were twenty-four thousand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 25:10"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 25:11"}, "\u201cPhinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Harun the priest, has turned my wrath away from the children of Israel, in that\nhe was jealous with my jealousy amongst them, so that I didn\u2019t consume the children of Israel in my jealousy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 25:12"}, "Therefore say, \u2018Behold, I give to him my covenant of peace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 25:13"}, "It shall be to him, and to his offspring after him, the covenant of an everlasting priesthood, because he was jealous for\nhis Allah, and made atonement for the children of Israel.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 25:14"}, "Now the name of the man of Israel that was slain, who was slain with the Midianite woman, was Zimri, the son of Salu, a\nprince of a fathers\u2019 house amongst the Simeonites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 25:15"}, "The name of the Midianite woman who was slain was Cozbi, the daughter of Zur. He was head of the people of a fathers\u2019\nhouse in Midian. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 25:16"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 25:17"}, "\u201cHarass the Midianites, and strike them; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 25:18"}, "for they harassed you with their wiles, wherein they have deceived you in the matter of Peor, and in the incident\nregarding Cozbi, the daughter of the prince of Midian, their sister, who was slain on the day of the plague in the matter of\nPeor.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 26:1"}, "After the plague, the LORD spoke to Musa and to Eleazar the son of Harun the priest, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 26:2"}, "\u201cTake a census of all the congregation of the children of Israel, from twenty years old and upward, by their fathers\u2019\nhouses, all who are able to go out to war in Israel.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 26:3"}, "Musa and Eleazar the priest spoke with them in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 26:4"}, "\u201cTake a census, from twenty years old and upward, as the LORD commanded Musa and the children of Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["These are those that came out of the land of Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 26:5"}, "Reuben, the firstborn of Israel; the sons of Reuben: of Hanoch, the family of the Hanochites; of Pallu, the family of the\nPalluites; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 26:6"}, "of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites; of Carmi, the family of the Carmites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 26:7"}, "These are the families of the Reubenites; and those who were counted of them were forty-three thousand and seven hundred\nand thirty. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 26:8"}, "The son of Pallu: Eliab. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 26:9"}, "The sons of Eliab: Nemuel, Dathan, and Abiram. These are that Dathan and Abiram who were called by the congregation, who\nrebelled against Musa and against Harun in the company of Korah when they rebelled against the LORD;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 26:10"}, "and the earth opened its mouth, and swallowed them up together with Korah when that company died; at the time the fire\ndevoured two hundred and fifty men, and they became a sign. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 26:11"}, "Notwithstanding, the sons of Korah didn\u2019t die. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 26:12"}, "The sons of Simeon after their families: of Nemuel, the family of the Nemuelites; of Jamin, the family of the Jaminites;\nof Jachin, the family of the Jachinites; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 26:13"}, "of Zerah, the family of the Zerahites; of Shaul, the family of the Shaulites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 26:14"}, "These are the families of the Simeonites, twenty-two thousand and two hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 26:15"}, "The sons of Gad after their families: of Zephon, the family of the Zephonites; of Haggi, the family of the Haggites; of\nShuni, the family of the Shunites; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 26:16"}, "of Ozni, the family of the Oznites; of Eri, the family of the Erites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 26:17"}, "of Arod, the family of the Arodites; of Areli, the family of the Arelites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 26:18"}, "These are the families of the sons of Gad according to those who were counted of them, forty thousand and five hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 26:19"}, "The sons of Judah: Er and Onan. Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 26:20"}, "The sons of Judah after their families were: of Shelah, the family of the Shelanites; of Perez, the family of the\nPerezites; of Zerah, the family of the Zerahites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 26:21"}, "The sons of Perez were: of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites; of Hamul, the family of the Hamulites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 26:22"}, "These are the families of Judah according to those who were counted of them, seventy-six thousand and five hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 26:23"}, "The sons of Issachar after their families: of Tola, the family of the Tolaites; of Puvah, the family of the Punites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 26:24"}, "of Jashub, the family of the Jashubites; of Shimron, the family of the Shimronites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 26:25"}, "These are the families of Issachar according to those who were counted of them, sixty-four thousand and three hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 26:26"}, "The sons of Zebulun after their families: of Sered, the family of the Seredites; of Elon, the family of the Elonites; of\nJahleel, the family of the Jahleelites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 26:27"}, "These are the families of the Zebulunites according to those who were counted of them, sixty thousand and five hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 26:28"}, "The sons of Yusuf after their families: Manasseh and Ephraim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 26:29"}, "The sons of Manasseh: of Machir, the family of the Machirites; and Machir became the father of Gilead; of Gilead, the\nfamily of the Gileadites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 26:30"}, "These are the sons of Gilead: of Iezer, the family of the Iezerites; of Helek, the family of the Helekites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 26:31"}, "and Asriel, the family of the Asrielites; and Shechem, the family of the Shechemites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 26:32"}, "and Shemida, the family of the Shemidaites; and Hepher, the family of the Hepherites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 26:33"}, "Zelophehad the son of Hepher had no sons, but daughters: and the names of the daughters of Zelophehad were Mahlah, Nuh,\nHoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 26:34"}, "These are the families of Manasseh. Those who were counted of them were fifty-two thousand and seven hundred.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 26:35"}, "These are the sons of Ephraim after their families: of Shuthelah, the family of the Shuthelahites; of Becher, the family\nof the Becherites; of Tahan, the family of the Tahanites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 26:36"}, "These are the sons of Shuthelah: of Eran, the family of the Eranites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 26:37"}, "These are the families of the sons of Ephraim according to those who were counted of them, thirty-two thousand and five\nhundred. These are the sons of Yusuf after their families. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 26:38"}, "The sons of Benjamin after their families: of Bela, the family of the Belaites; of Ashbel, the family of the Ashbelites;\nof Ahiram, the family of the Ahiramites; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 26:39"}, "of Shephupham, the family of the Shuphamites; of Hupham, the family of the Huphamites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 26:40"}, "The sons of Bela were Ard and Naaman: the family of the Ardites; and of Naaman, the family of the Naamites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 26:41"}, "These are the sons of Benjamin after their families; and those who were counted of them were forty-five thousand and six\nhundred. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 26:42"}, "These are the sons of Dan after their families: of Shuham, the family of the Shuhamites. These are the families of Dan\nafter their families. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 26:43"}, "All the families of the Shuhamites, according to those who were counted of them, were sixty-four thousand and four\nhundred. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 26:44"}, "The sons of Asher after their families: of Imnah, the family of the Imnites; of Ishvi, the family of the Ishvites; of\nBeriah, the family of the Berites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 26:45"}, "Of the sons of Beriah: of Heber, the family of the Heberites; of Malchiel, the family of the Malchielites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 26:46"}, "The name of the daughter of Asher was Serah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 26:47"}, "These are the families of the sons of Asher according to those who were counted of them, fifty-three thousand and four\nhundred. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 26:48"}, "The sons of Naphtali after their families: of Jahzeel, the family of the Jahzeelites; of Guni, the family of the Gunites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 26:49"}, "of Jezer, the family of the Jezerites; of Shillem, the family of the Shillemites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 26:50"}, "These are the families of Naphtali according to their families; and those who were counted of them were forty-five\nthousand and four hundred. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "NUM 26:51"}, "These are those who were counted of the children of Israel, six hundred and one thousand and seven hundred and thirty.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "NUM 26:52"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "NUM 26:53"}, "\u201cTo these the land shall be divided for an inheritance according to the number of names.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "NUM 26:54"}, "To the more you shall give the more inheritance, and to the fewer you shall give the less inheritance. To everyone\naccording to those who were counted of him shall his inheritance be given.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "NUM 26:55"}, "Notwithstanding, the land shall be divided by lot. According to the names of the tribes of their fathers they shall\ninherit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "NUM 26:56"}, "According to the lot shall their inheritance be divided between the more and the fewer.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "NUM 26:57"}, "These are those who were counted of the Levites after their families: of Gershon, the family of the Gershonites; of\nKohath, the family of the Kohathites; of Merari, the family of the Merarites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "NUM 26:58"}, "These are the families of Levi: the family of the Libnites, the family of the Hebronites, the family of the Mahlites, the\nfamily of the Mushites, and the family of the Korahites. Kohath became the father of Amram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "NUM 26:59"}, "The name of Amram\u2019s wife was Jochebed, the daughter of Levi, who was born to Levi in Egypt. She bore to Amram Harun and\nMusa, and Miriam their sister. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "NUM 26:60"}, "To Harun were born Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "NUM 26:61"}, "Nadab and Abihu died when they offered strange fire before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "NUM 26:62"}, "Those who were counted of them were twenty-three thousand, every male from a month old and upward; for they were not\ncounted amongst the children of Israel, because there was no inheritance given them amongst the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "NUM 26:63"}, "These are those who were counted by Musa and Eleazar the priest, who counted the children of Israel in the plains of Moab\nby the Jordan at Jericho. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "NUM 26:64"}, "But amongst these there was not a man of them who were counted by Musa and Harun the priest, who counted the children of\nIsrael in the wilderness of Sinai. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "NUM 26:65"}, "For the LORD had said of them, \u201cThey shall surely die in the wilderness.\u201d There was not a man left of them, except Caleb\nthe son of Jephunneh, and Joshua the son of Nun. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 27:1"}, "Then the daughters of Zelophehad, the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of the\nfamilies of Manasseh the son of Yusuf came near. These are the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Nuh, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 27:2"}, "They stood before Musa, before Eleazar the priest, and before the princes and all the congregation, at the door of the\nTent of Meeting, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 27:3"}, "\u201cOur father died in the wilderness. He was not amongst the company of those who gathered themselves together against the\nLORD in the company of Korah, but he died in his own sin. He had no sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 27:4"}, "Why should the name of our father be taken away from amongst his family, because he had no son? Give to us a possession\namongst the brothers of our father.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 27:5"}, "Musa brought their cause before the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 27:6"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 27:7"}, "\u201cThe daughters of Zelophehad speak right. You shall surely give them a possession of an inheritance amongst their father\u2019s\nbrothers. You shall cause the inheritance of their father to pass to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 27:8"}, "You shall speak to the children of Israel, saying, \u2018If a man dies, and has no son, then you shall cause his inheritance to\npass to his daughter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 27:9"}, "If he has no daughter, then you shall give his inheritance to his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 27:10"}, "If he has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his father\u2019s brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 27:11"}, "If his father has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his kinsman who is next to him of his family, and\nhe shall possess it. This shall be a statute and ordinance for the children of Israel, as the LORD commanded Musa.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 27:12"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cGo up into this mountain of Abarim, and see the land which I have given to the children of\nIsrael. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 27:13"}, "When you have seen it, you also shall be gathered to your people, as Harun your brother was gathered;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 27:14"}, "because in the strife of the congregation, you rebelled against my word in the wilderness of Zin, to honour me as holy at\nthe waters before their eyes.\u201d (These are the waters of Meribah of Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.)\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 27:15"}, "Musa spoke to the LORD, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 27:16"}, "\u201cLet the LORD, Allah of the spirits of all flesh, appoint a man over the congregation,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 27:17"}, "who may go out before them, and who may come in before them, and who may lead them out, and who may bring them in, that\nthe congregation of the LORD may not be as sheep which have no shepherd.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 27:18"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cTake Joshua the son of Nun, a man in whom is the Spirit, and lay your hand on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 27:19"}, "Set him before Eleazar the priest, and before all the congregation; and commission him in their sight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 27:20"}, "You shall give authority to him, that all the congregation of the children of Israel may obey.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 27:21"}, "He shall stand before Eleazar the priest, who shall enquire for him by the judgement of the Urim before the LORD. At his\nword they shall go out, and at his word they shall come in, both he and all the children of Israel with him, even all the\ncongregation.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 27:22"}, "Musa did as the LORD commanded him. He took Joshua, and set him before Eleazar the priest and before all the\ncongregation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 27:23"}, "He laid his hands on him and commissioned him, as the LORD spoke by Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 28:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 28:2"}, "\u201cCommand the children of Israel, and tell them, \u2018See that you present my offering, my food for my offerings made by fire,\nas a pleasant aroma to me, in their due season.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 28:3"}, "You shall tell them, \u2018This is the offering made by fire which you shall offer to the LORD: male lambs a year old without\ndefect, two day by day, for a continual burnt offering. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 28:4"}, "You shall offer the one lamb in the morning, and you shall offer the other lamb at evening,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 28:5"}, "with one tenth of an ephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine flour for a meal offering, mixed with the fourth part of a\nhin", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A hin is about 6.5 litres or 1.7 gallons."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of beaten oil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 28:6"}, "It is a continual burnt offering which was ordained in Mount Sinai for a pleasant aroma, an offering made by fire to the\nLORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 28:7"}, "Its drink offering shall be the fourth part of a hin", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:7\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["One hin is about 6.5 litres, so 1/4 hin is about 1.6 litres or 1.7\nquarts."]}], "caller": "+"}, " for each lamb. You shall pour out a drink offering of strong drink to the LORD in the holy place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 28:8"}, "The other lamb you shall offer at evening. As the meal offering of the morning, and as its drink offering, you shall offer\nit, an offering made by fire, for a pleasant aroma to the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 28:9"}, "\u201c\u2018On the Sabbath day, you shall offer two male lambs a year old without defect, and two tenths of an\nephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine flour for a meal offering mixed with oil, and its drink offering:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 28:10"}, "this is the burnt offering of every Sabbath, in addition to the continual burnt offering and its drink offering.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 28:11"}, "\u201c\u2018In the beginnings of your months, you shall offer a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, seven male\nlambs a year old without defect, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 28:12"}, "and three tenths of an ephah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine flour for a meal offering mixed with oil, for each bull; and two tenth parts of fine flour for a meal\noffering mixed with oil, for the one ram; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 28:13"}, "and one tenth part of fine flour mixed with oil for a meal offering to every lamb, as a burnt offering of a pleasant\naroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 28:14"}, "Their drink offerings shall be half a hin of wine for a bull, the third part of a hin for the ram, and the fourth part of\na hin for a lamb. This is the burnt offering of every month throughout the months of the year.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 28:15"}, "Also, one male goat for a sin offering to the LORD shall be offered in addition to the continual burnt offering and its\ndrink offering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 28:16"}, "\u201c\u2018In the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month, is the LORD\u2019s Passover.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 28:17"}, "On the fifteenth day of this month shall be a feast. Unleavened bread shall be eaten for seven days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 28:18"}, "In the first day shall be a holy convocation. You shall do no regular work,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 28:19"}, "but you shall offer an offering made by fire, a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven male\nlambs a year old. They shall be without defect, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 28:20"}, "with their meal offering, fine flour mixed with oil. You shall offer three tenths for a bull, and two tenths for the ram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 28:21"}, "You shall offer one tenth for every lamb of the seven lambs;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 28:22"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 28:23"}, "You shall offer these in addition to the burnt offering of the morning, which is for a continual burnt offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 28:24"}, "In this way you shall offer daily, for seven days, the food of the offering made by fire, of a pleasant aroma to the\nLORD. It shall be offered in addition to the continual burnt offering and its drink offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 28:25"}, "On the seventh day you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no regular work.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 28:26"}, "\u201c\u2018Also in the day of the first fruits, when you offer a new meal offering to the LORD in your feast of weeks, you shall\nhave a holy convocation. You shall do no regular work; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 28:27"}, "but you shall offer a burnt offering for a pleasant aroma to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, seven male lambs a year\nold; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 28:28"}, "and their meal offering, fine flour mixed with oil, three tenths for each bull, two tenths for the one ram,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 28:29"}, "one tenth for every lamb of the seven lambs; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 28:30"}, "and one male goat, to make atonement for you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 28:31"}, "Besides the continual burnt offering and its meal offering, you shall offer them and their drink offerings. See that they\nare without defect. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 29"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 29:1"}, "\u201c\u2018In the seventh month, on the first day of the month, you shall have a holy convocation; you shall do no regular work. It\nis a day of blowing of trumpets to you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 29:2"}, "You shall offer a burnt offering for a pleasant aroma to the LORD: one young bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year old\nwithout defect; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 29:3"}, "and their meal offering, fine flour mixed with oil: three tenths for the bull, two tenths for the ram,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 29:4"}, "and one tenth for every lamb of the seven lambs; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 29:5"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 29:6"}, "in addition to the burnt offering of the new moon with its meal offering, and the continual burnt offering with its meal\noffering, and their drink offerings, according to their ordinance, for a pleasant aroma, an offering made by fire to the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 29:7"}, "\u201c\u2018On the tenth day of this seventh month you shall have a holy convocation. You shall afflict your souls. You shall do no\nkind of work; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 29:8"}, "but you shall offer a burnt offering to the LORD for a pleasant aroma: one young bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year\nold, all without defect; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 29:9"}, "and their meal offering, fine flour mixed with oil: three tenths for the bull, two tenths for the one ram,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 29:10"}, "one tenth for every lamb of the seven lambs; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 29:11"}, "one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the sin offering of atonement, and the continual burnt offering, and its\nmeal offering, and their drink offerings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 29:12"}, "\u201c\u2018On the fifteenth day of the seventh month you shall have a holy convocation. You shall do no regular work. You shall\nkeep a feast to the LORD seven days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 29:13"}, "You shall offer a burnt offering, an offering made by fire, of a pleasant aroma to the LORD: thirteen young bulls, two\nrams, fourteen male lambs a year old, all without defect; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 29:14"}, "and their meal offering, fine flour mixed with oil: three tenths for every bull of the thirteen bulls, two tenths for\neach ram of the two rams, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 29:15"}, "and one tenth for every lamb of the fourteen lambs; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 29:16"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, its meal offering, and its drink\noffering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 29:17"}, "\u201c\u2018On the second day you shall offer twelve young bulls, two rams, and fourteen male lambs a year old without defect;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 29:18"}, "and their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, according to their\nnumber, after the ordinance; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 29:19"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, with its meal offering and their drink\nofferings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 29:20"}, "\u201c\u2018On the third day: eleven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without defect;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 29:21"}, "and their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, according to their\nnumber, after the ordinance; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 29:22"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, and its meal offering, and its drink\noffering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 29:23"}, "\u201c\u2018On the fourth day ten bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without defect;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 29:24"}, "their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, according to their number,\nafter the ordinance; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 29:25"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering; in addition to the continual burnt offering, its meal offering, and its drink\noffering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 29:26"}, "\u201c\u2018On the fifth day: nine bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without defect;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 29:27"}, "and their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, according to their\nnumber, after the ordinance, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 29:28"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, and its meal offering, and its drink\noffering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 29:29"}, "\u201c\u2018On the sixth day: eight bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without defect;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 29:30"}, "and their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, according to their\nnumber, after the ordinance, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 29:31"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering; in addition to the continual burnt offering, its meal offering, and the drink\nofferings of it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 29:32"}, "\u201c\u2018On the seventh day: seven bulls, two rams, fourteen male lambs a year old without defect;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 29:33"}, "and their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bulls, for the rams, and for the lambs, according to their\nnumber, after the ordinance, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 29:34"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering; in addition to the continual burnt offering, its meal offering, and its drink\noffering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 29:35"}, "\u201c\u2018On the eighth day you shall have a solemn assembly. You shall do no regular work;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 29:36"}, "but you shall offer a burnt offering, an offering made by fire, a pleasant aroma to the LORD: one bull, one ram, seven\nmale lambs a year old without defect; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 29:37"}, "their meal offering and their drink offerings for the bull, for the ram, and for the lambs, shall be according to their\nnumber, after the ordinance, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 29:38"}, "and one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the continual burnt offering, with its meal offering, and its drink\noffering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 29:39"}, "\u201c\u2018You shall offer these to the LORD in your set feasts\u2014in addition to your vows and your free will offerings\u2014for your\nburnt offerings, your meal offerings, your drink offerings, and your peace offerings.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 29:40"}, "Musa told the children of Israel according to all that the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 30"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 30:1"}, "Musa spoke to the heads of the tribes of the children of Israel, saying, \u201cThis is the thing which the LORD has commanded.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 30:2"}, "When a man vows a vow to the LORD, or swears an oath to bind his soul with a bond, he shall not break his word. He shall\ndo according to all that proceeds out of his mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 30:3"}, "\u201cAlso, when a woman vows a vow to the LORD and binds herself by a pledge, being in her father\u2019s house, in her youth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 30:4"}, "and her father hears her vow and her pledge with which she has bound her soul, and her father says nothing to her, then\nall her vows shall stand, and every pledge with which she has bound her soul shall stand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 30:5"}, "But if her father forbids her in the day that he hears, none of her vows or of her pledges with which she has bound her\nsoul, shall stand. The LORD will forgive her, because her father has forbidden her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 30:6"}, "\u201cIf she has a husband, while her vows are on her, or the rash utterance of her lips with which she has bound her soul,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 30:7"}, "and her husband hears it, and says nothing to her in the day that he hears it; then her vows shall stand, and her pledges\nwith which she has bound her soul shall stand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 30:8"}, "But if her husband forbids her in the day that he hears it, then he makes void her vow which is on her and the rash\nutterance of her lips, with which she has bound her soul. The LORD will forgive her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 30:9"}, "\u201cBut the vow of a widow, or of her who is divorced, everything with which she has bound her soul shall stand against her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 30:10"}, "\u201cIf she vowed in her husband\u2019s house or bound her soul by a bond with an oath,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 30:11"}, "and her husband heard it, and held his peace at her and didn\u2019t disallow her, then all her vows shall stand, and every\npledge with which she bound her soul shall stand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 30:12"}, "But if her husband made them null and void in the day that he heard them, then whatever proceeded out of her lips\nconcerning her vows, or concerning the bond of her soul, shall not stand. Her husband has made them void. The LORD will forgive\nher. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 30:13"}, "Every vow, and every binding oath to afflict the soul, her husband may establish it, or her husband may make it void.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 30:14"}, "But if her husband says nothing to her from day to day, then he establishes all her vows or all her pledges which are on\nher. He has established them, because he said nothing to her in the day that he heard them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 30:15"}, "But if he makes them null and void after he has heard them, then he shall bear her iniquity.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 30:16"}, "These are the statutes which the LORD commanded Musa, between a man and his wife, between a father and his daughter,\nbeing in her youth, in her father\u2019s house. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 31"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 31:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 31:2"}, "\u201cAvenge the children of Israel on the Midianites. Afterward you shall be gathered to your people.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 31:3"}, "Musa spoke to the people, saying, \u201cArm men from amongst you for war, that they may go against Midian, to execute the\nLORD\u2019s vengeance on Midian. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 31:4"}, "You shall send one thousand out of every tribe, throughout all the tribes of Israel, to the war.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 31:5"}, "So there were delivered, out of the thousands of Israel, a thousand from every tribe, twelve thousand armed for war.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 31:6"}, "Musa sent them, one thousand of every tribe, to the war with Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, to the war, with the\nvessels of the sanctuary and the trumpets for the alarm in his hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 31:7"}, "They fought against Midian, as the LORD commanded Musa. They killed every male.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 31:8"}, "They killed the kings of Midian with the rest of their slain: Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba, the five kings of Midian.\nThey also killed Balaam the son of Beor with the sword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 31:9"}, "The children of Israel took the women of Midian captive with their little ones; and all their livestock, all their flocks,\nand all their goods, they took as plunder. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 31:10"}, "All their cities in the places in which they lived, and all their encampments, they burnt with fire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 31:11"}, "They took all the captives, and all the plunder, both of man and of animal.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 31:12"}, "They brought the captives with the prey and the plunder, to Musa, and to Eleazar the priest, and to the congregation of\nthe children of Israel, to the camp at the plains of Moab, which are by the Jordan at Jericho.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 31:13"}, "Musa and Eleazar the priest, with all the princes of the congregation, went out to meet them outside of the camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 31:14"}, "Musa was angry with the officers of the army, the captains of thousands and the captains of hundreds, who came from the\nservice of the war. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 31:15"}, "Musa said to them, \u201cHave you saved all the women alive? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 31:16"}, "Behold, these caused the children of Israel, through the counsel of Balaam, to commit trespass against the LORD in the\nmatter of Peor, and so the plague was amongst the congregation of the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 31:17"}, "Now therefore kill every male amongst the little ones, and kill every woman who has known man by lying with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 31:18"}, "But all the girls, who have not known man by lying with him, keep alive for yourselves.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 31:19"}, "\u201cEncamp outside of the camp for seven days. Whoever has killed any person, and whoever has touched any slain, purify\nyourselves on the third day and on the seventh day, you and your captives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 31:20"}, "You shall purify every garment, and all that is made of skin, and all work of goats\u2019 hair, and all things made of wood.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 31:21"}, "Eleazar the priest said to the men of war who went to the battle, \u201cThis is the statute of the law which the LORD has\ncommanded Musa: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 31:22"}, "however the gold, and the silver, the bronze, the iron, the tin, and the lead,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 31:23"}, "everything that may withstand the fire, you shall make to go through the fire, and it shall be clean; nevertheless it\nshall be purified with the water for impurity. All that doesn\u2019t withstand the fire you shall make to go through the water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 31:24"}, "You shall wash your clothes on the seventh day, and you shall be clean. Afterward you shall come into the camp.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 31:25"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 31:26"}, "\u201cCount the plunder that was taken, both of man and of animal, you, and Eleazar the priest, and the heads of the fathers\u2019\nhouseholds of the congregation; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 31:27"}, "and divide the plunder into two parts: between the men skilled in war, who went out to battle, and all the congregation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 31:28"}, "Levy a tribute to the LORD of the men of war who went out to battle: one soul of five hundred; of the persons, of the\ncattle, of the donkeys, and of the flocks. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 31:29"}, "Take it from their half, and give it to Eleazar the priest, for the LORD\u2019s wave offering.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 31:30"}, "Of the children of Israel\u2019s half, you shall take one drawn out of every fifty, of the persons, of the cattle, of the\ndonkeys, and of the flocks, of all the livestock, and give them to the Levites, who perform the duty of the LORD\u2019s tabernacle.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 31:31"}, "Musa and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 31:32"}, "Now the plunder, over and above the booty which the men of war took, was six hundred and seventy-five thousand sheep,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 31:33"}, "seventy-two thousand head of cattle, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 31:34"}, "sixty-one thousand donkeys, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 31:35"}, "and thirty-two thousand persons in all, of the women who had not known man by lying with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 31:36"}, "The half, which was the portion of those who went out to war, was in number three hundred and thirty-seven thousand and\nfive hundred sheep; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 31:37"}, "and the LORD\u2019s tribute of the sheep was six hundred and seventy-five.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 31:38"}, "The cattle were thirty-six thousand, of which the LORD\u2019s tribute was seventy-two.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 31:39"}, "The donkeys were thirty thousand and five hundred, of which the LORD\u2019s tribute was sixty-one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 31:40"}, "The persons were sixteen thousand, of whom the LORD\u2019s tribute was thirty-two persons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 31:41"}, "Musa gave the tribute, which was the LORD\u2019s wave offering, to Eleazar the priest, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 31:42"}, "Of the children of Israel\u2019s half, which Musa divided off from the men who fought\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 31:43"}, "(now the congregation\u2019s half was three hundred and thirty-seven thousand and five hundred sheep,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 31:44"}, "thirty-six thousand head of cattle, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 31:45"}, "thirty thousand and five hundred donkeys, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 31:46"}, "and sixteen thousand persons), \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 31:47"}, "even of the children of Israel\u2019s half, Musa took one drawn out of every fifty, both of man and of animal, and gave them\nto the Levites, who performed the duty of the LORD\u2019s tabernacle, as the LORD commanded Musa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 31:48"}, "The officers who were over the thousands of the army, the captains of thousands, and the captains of hundreds, came near\nto Musa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 31:49"}, "They said to Musa, \u201cYour servants have taken the sum of the men of war who are under our command, and there lacks not one\nman of us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 31:50"}, "We have brought the LORD\u2019s offering, what every man found: gold ornaments, armlets, bracelets, signet rings, earrings,\nand necklaces, to make atonement for our souls before the LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "NUM 31:51"}, "Musa and Eleazar the priest took their gold, even all worked jewels.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "NUM 31:52"}, "All the gold of the wave offering that they offered up to the LORD, of the captains of thousands, and of the captains of\nhundreds, was sixteen thousand and seven hundred and fifty shekels.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["31:52 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 16,750 shekels is about 167.5 kilograms or about 368.5\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "NUM 31:53"}, "The men of war had taken booty, every man for himself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "NUM 31:54"}, "Musa and Eleazar the priest took the gold of the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it into the Tent of\nMeeting for a memorial for the children of Israel before the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 32"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 32:1"}, "Now the children of Reuben and the children of Gad had a very great multitude of livestock. They saw the land of Jazer,\nand the land of Gilead. Behold, the place was a place for livestock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 32:2"}, "Then the children of Gad and the children of Reuben came and spoke to Musa, and to Eleazar the priest, and to the princes\nof the congregation, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 32:3"}, "\u201cAtaroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sebam, Nebo, and Beon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 32:4"}, "the land which The LORD struck before the congregation of Israel, is a land for livestock; and your servants have\nlivestock.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 32:5"}, "They said, \u201cIf we have found favour in your sight, let this land be given to your servants for a possession. Don\u2019t bring\nus over the Jordan.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 32:6"}, "Musa said to the children of Gad, and to the children of Reuben, \u201cShall your brothers go to war while you sit here?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 32:7"}, "Why do you discourage the heart of the children of Israel from going over into the land which the LORD has given them?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 32:8"}, "Your fathers did so when I sent them from Kadesh Barnea to see the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 32:9"}, "For when they went up to the valley of Eshcol, and saw the land, they discouraged the heart of the children of Israel,\nthat they should not go into the land which the LORD had given them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 32:10"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt in that day, and he swore, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 32:11"}, "\u2018Surely none of the men who came up out of Egypt, from twenty years old and upward, shall see the land which I swore to\nIbrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub; because they have not wholly followed me,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 32:12"}, "except Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite, and Joshua the son of Nun, because they have followed the LORD\ncompletely.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 32:13"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel, and he made them wander back and forth in the wilderness forty years, until all\nthe generation who had done evil in the LORD\u2019s sight was consumed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 32:14"}, "\u201cBehold, you have risen up in your fathers\u2019 place, an increase of sinful men, to increase the fierce anger of the LORD\ntowards Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 32:15"}, "For if you turn away from after him, he will yet again leave them in the wilderness; and you will destroy all these\npeople.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 32:16"}, "They came near to him, and said, \u201cWe will build sheepfolds here for our livestock, and cities for our little ones;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 32:17"}, "but we ourselves will be ready armed to go before the children of Israel, until we have brought them to their place. Our\nlittle ones shall dwell in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 32:18"}, "We will not return to our houses until the children of Israel have all received their inheritance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 32:19"}, "For we will not inherit with them on the other side of the Jordan and beyond, because our inheritance has come to us on\nthis side of the Jordan eastward.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 32:20"}, "Musa said to them: \u201cIf you will do this thing, if you will arm yourselves to go before the LORD to the war,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 32:21"}, "and every one of your armed men will pass over the Jordan before the LORD until he has driven out his enemies from before\nhim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 32:22"}, "and the land is subdued before the LORD; then afterward you shall return, and be clear of obligation to the LORD and to\nIsrael. Then this land shall be your possession before the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 32:23"}, "\u201cBut if you will not do so, behold, you have sinned against the LORD; and be sure your sin will find you out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 32:24"}, "Build cities for your little ones, and folds for your sheep; and do that which has proceeded out of your mouth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 32:25"}, "The children of Gad and the children of Reuben spoke to Musa, saying, \u201cYour servants will do as my lord commands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 32:26"}, "Our little ones, our wives, our flocks, and all our livestock shall be there in the cities of Gilead;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 32:27"}, "but your servants will pass over, every man who is armed for war, before the LORD to battle, as my lord says.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 32:28"}, "So Musa commanded concerning them to Eleazar the priest, and to Joshua the son of Nun, and to the heads of the fathers\u2019\nhouseholds of the tribes of the children of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 32:29"}, "Musa said to them, \u201cIf the children of Gad and the children of Reuben will pass with you over the Jordan, every man who\nis armed to battle before the LORD, and the land is subdued before you, then you shall give them the land of Gilead for a\npossession; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 32:30"}, "but if they will not pass over with you armed, they shall have possessions amongst you in the land of Canaan.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 32:31"}, "The children of Gad and the children of Reuben answered, saying, \u201cAs the LORD has said to your servants, so will we do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 32:32"}, "We will pass over armed before the LORD into the land of Canaan, and the possession of our inheritance shall remain with\nus beyond the Jordan.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 32:33"}, "Musa gave to them, even to the children of Gad, and to the children of Reuben, and to the half-tribe of Manasseh the son\nof Yusuf, the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites, and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan; the land, according to its cities\nand borders, even the cities of the surrounding land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 32:34"}, "The children of Gad built Dibon, Ataroth, Aroer, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 32:35"}, "Atroth-shophan, Jazer, Jogbehah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 32:36"}, "Beth Nimrah, and Beth Haran: fortified cities and folds for sheep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 32:37"}, "The children of Reuben built Heshbon, Elealeh, Kiriathaim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 32:38"}, "Nebo, and Baal Meon, (their names being changed), and Sibmah. They gave other names to the cities which they built.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 32:39"}, "The children of Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead, took it, and dispossessed the Amorites who were therein.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 32:40"}, "Musa gave Gilead to Machir the son of Manasseh; and he lived therein.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 32:41"}, "Jair the son of Manasseh went and took its villages, and called them Havvoth Jair.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 32:42"}, "Nobah went and took Kenath and its villages, and called it Nobah, after his own name.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 33"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 33:1"}, "These are the journeys of the children of Israel, when they went out of the land of Egypt by their armies under the hand\nof Musa and Harun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 33:2"}, "Musa wrote the starting points of their journeys by the commandment of the LORD. These are their journeys according to\ntheir starting points. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 33:3"}, "They travelled from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; on the next day after the\nPassover, the children of Israel went out with a high hand in the sight of all the Egyptians,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 33:4"}, "while the Egyptians were burying all their firstborn, whom the LORD had struck amongst them. The LORD also executed\njudgements on their gods. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 33:5"}, "The children of Israel travelled from Rameses, and encamped in Succoth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 33:6"}, "They travelled from Succoth, and encamped in Etham, which is in the edge of the wilderness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 33:7"}, "They travelled from Etham, and turned back to Pihahiroth, which is before Baal Zephon, and they encamped before Migdol.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 33:8"}, "They travelled from before Hahiroth, and crossed through the middle of the sea into the wilderness. They went three days\u2019\njourney in the wilderness of Etham, and encamped in Marah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 33:9"}, "They travelled from Marah, and came to Elim. In Elim, there were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees, and they\nencamped there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 33:10"}, "They travelled from Elim, and encamped by the Red Sea. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 33:11"}, "They travelled from the Red Sea, and encamped in the wilderness of Sin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 33:12"}, "They travelled from the wilderness of Sin, and encamped in Dophkah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 33:13"}, "They travelled from Dophkah, and encamped in Alush. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 33:14"}, "They travelled from Alush, and encamped in Rephidim, where there was no water for the people to drink.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 33:15"}, "They travelled from Rephidim, and encamped in the wilderness of Sinai.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 33:16"}, "They travelled from the wilderness of Sinai, and encamped in Kibroth Hattaavah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 33:17"}, "They travelled from Kibroth Hattaavah, and encamped in Hazeroth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 33:18"}, "They travelled from Hazeroth, and encamped in Rithmah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 33:19"}, "They travelled from Rithmah, and encamped in Rimmon Perez.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 33:20"}, "They travelled from Rimmon Perez, and encamped in Libnah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 33:21"}, "They travelled from Libnah, and encamped in Rissah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 33:22"}, "They travelled from Rissah, and encamped in Kehelathah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 33:23"}, "They travelled from Kehelathah, and encamped in Mount Shepher.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 33:24"}, "They travelled from Mount Shepher, and encamped in Haradah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 33:25"}, "They travelled from Haradah, and encamped in Makheloth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 33:26"}, "They travelled from Makheloth, and encamped in Tahath. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 33:27"}, "They travelled from Tahath, and encamped in Terah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 33:28"}, "They travelled from Terah, and encamped in Mithkah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 33:29"}, "They travelled from Mithkah, and encamped in Hashmonah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 33:30"}, "They travelled from Hashmonah, and encamped in Moseroth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 33:31"}, "They travelled from Moseroth, and encamped in Bene Jaakan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 33:32"}, "They travelled from Bene Jaakan, and encamped in Hor Haggidgad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 33:33"}, "They travelled from Hor Haggidgad, and encamped in Jotbathah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 33:34"}, "They travelled from Jotbathah, and encamped in Abronah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 33:35"}, "They travelled from Abronah, and encamped in Ezion Geber. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 33:36"}, "They travelled from Ezion Geber, and encamped at Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "NUM 33:37"}, "They travelled from Kadesh, and encamped in Mount Hor, in the edge of the land of Edom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "NUM 33:38"}, "Harun the priest went up into Mount Hor at the commandment of the LORD and died there, in the fortieth year after the\nchildren of Israel had come out of the land of Egypt, in the fifth month, on the first day of the month.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "NUM 33:39"}, "Harun was one hundred and twenty-three years old when he died in Mount Hor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "NUM 33:40"}, "The Canaanite king of Arad, who lived in the South in the land of Canaan, heard of the coming of the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "NUM 33:41"}, "They travelled from Mount Hor, and encamped in Zalmonah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "NUM 33:42"}, "They travelled from Zalmonah, and encamped in Punon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "NUM 33:43"}, "They travelled from Punon, and encamped in Oboth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "NUM 33:44"}, "They travelled from Oboth, and encamped in Iye Abarim, in the border of Moab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "NUM 33:45"}, "They travelled from Iyim, and encamped in Dibon Gad. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "NUM 33:46"}, "They travelled from Dibon Gad, and encamped in Almon Diblathaim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "NUM 33:47"}, "They travelled from Almon Diblathaim, and encamped in the mountains of Abarim, before Nebo.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "NUM 33:48"}, "They travelled from the mountains of Abarim, and encamped in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "NUM 33:49"}, "They encamped by the Jordan, from Beth Jeshimoth even to Habil Shittim in the plains of Moab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "NUM 33:50"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "NUM 33:51"}, "Speak to the children of Israel, and tell them, \u201cWhen you pass over the Jordan into the land of Canaan,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "NUM 33:52"}, "then you shall drive out all the inhabitants of the land from before you, destroy all their stone idols, destroy all\ntheir molten images, and demolish all their high places. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "NUM 33:53"}, "You shall take possession of the land, and dwell therein; for I have given the land to you to possess it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "NUM 33:54"}, "You shall inherit the land by lot according to your families; to the more you shall give the more inheritance, and to the\nfewer you shall give the less inheritance. Wherever the lot falls to any man, that shall be his. You shall inherit according to\nthe tribes of your fathers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "NUM 33:55"}, "\u201cBut if you do not drive out the inhabitants of the land from before you, then those you let remain of them will be like\npricks in your eyes and thorns in your sides. They will harass you in the land in which you dwell.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "NUM 33:56"}, "It shall happen that as I thought to do to them, so I will do to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 34"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 34:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 34:2"}, "\u201cCommand the children of Israel, and tell them, \u2018When you come into the land of Canaan (this is the land that shall fall\nto you for an inheritance, even the land of Canaan according to its borders),\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 34:3"}, "then your south quarter shall be from the wilderness of Zin along by the side of Edom, and your south border shall be from\nthe end of the Salt Sea eastward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 34:4"}, "Your border shall turn about southward of the ascent of Akrabbim, and pass along to Zin; and it shall pass southward of\nKadesh Barnea; and it shall go from there to Hazar Addar, and pass along to Azmon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 34:5"}, "The border shall turn about from Azmon to the brook of Egypt, and it shall end at the sea.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 34:6"}, "\u201c\u2018For the western border, you shall have the great sea and its border. This shall be your west border.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 34:7"}, "\u201c\u2018This shall be your north border: from the great sea you shall mark out for yourselves Mount Hor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 34:8"}, "From Mount Hor you shall mark out to the entrance of Hamath; and the border shall pass by Zedad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 34:9"}, "Then the border shall go to Ziphron, and it shall end at Hazar Enan. This shall be your north border.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 34:10"}, "\u201c\u2018You shall mark out your east border from Hazar Enan to Shepham.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 34:11"}, "The border shall go down from Shepham to Riblah, on the east side of Ain. The border shall go down, and shall reach to\nthe side of the sea of Chinnereth eastward. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 34:12"}, "The border shall go down to the Jordan, and end at the Salt Sea. This shall be your land according to its borders around\nit.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 34:13"}, "Musa commanded the children of Israel, saying, \u201cThis is the land which you shall inherit by lot, which the LORD has\ncommanded to give to the nine tribes, and to the half-tribe; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 34:14"}, "for the tribe of the children of Reuben according to their fathers\u2019 houses, the tribe of the children of Gad according to\ntheir fathers\u2019 houses, and the half-tribe of Manasseh have received their inheritance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 34:15"}, "The two tribes and the half-tribe have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan at Jericho eastward, towards the\nsunrise.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 34:16"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 34:17"}, "\u201cThese are the names of the men who shall divide the land to you for inheritance: Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son\nof Nun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 34:18"}, "You shall take one prince of every tribe, to divide the land for inheritance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 34:19"}, "These are the names of the men: Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 34:20"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Simeon, Shemuel the son of Ammihud.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 34:21"}, "Of the tribe of Benjamin, Elidad the son of Chislon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 34:22"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Dan a prince, Bukki the son of Jogli.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 34:23"}, "Of the children of Yusuf: of the tribe of the children of Manasseh a prince, Hanniel the son of Ephod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 34:24"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Ephraim a prince, Kemuel the son of Shiphtan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 34:25"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Zebulun a prince, Elizaphan the son of Parnach.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 34:26"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Issachar a prince, Paltiel the son of Azzan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 34:27"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Asher a prince, Ahihud the son of Shelomi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 34:28"}, "Of the tribe of the children of Naphtali a prince, Pedahel the son of Ammihud.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 34:29"}, "These are they whom the LORD commanded to divide the inheritance to the children of Israel in the land of Canaan.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "35", "sid": "NUM 35"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 35:1"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa in the plains of Moab by the Jordan at Jericho, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 35:2"}, "\u201cCommand the children of Israel to give to the Levites cities to dwell in out of their inheritance. You shall give pasture\nlands for the cities around them to the Levites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 35:3"}, "They shall have the cities to dwell in. Their pasture lands shall be for their livestock, and for their possessions, and\nfor all their animals. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 35:4"}, "\u201cThe pasture lands of the cities, which you shall give to the Levites, shall be from the wall of the city and outward one\nthousand cubits", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["35:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about\n18 inches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " around it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 35:5"}, "You shall measure outside of the city for the east side two thousand cubits, and for the south side two thousand cubits,\nand for the west side two thousand cubits, and for the north side two thousand cubits, the city being in the middle. This shall\nbe the pasture lands of their cities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 35:6"}, "\u201cThe cities which you shall give to the Levites, they shall be the six cities of refuge, which you shall give for the man\nslayer to flee to. Besides them you shall give forty-two cities.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 35:7"}, "All the cities which you shall give to the Levites shall be forty-eight cities together with their pasture lands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 35:8"}, "Concerning the cities which you shall give of the possession of the children of Israel, from the many you shall take many,\nand from the few you shall take few. Everyone according to his inheritance which he inherits shall give some of his cities to\nthe Levites.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 35:9"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 35:10"}, "\u201cSpeak to the children of Israel, and tell them, \u2018When you pass over the Jordan into the land of Canaan,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 35:11"}, "then you shall appoint for yourselves cities to be cities of refuge for you, that the man slayer who kills any person\nunwittingly may flee there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 35:12"}, "The cities shall be for your refuge from the avenger, that the man slayer not die until he stands before the congregation\nfor judgement. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 35:13"}, "The cities which you shall give shall be for you six cities of refuge.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NUM 35:14"}, "You shall give three cities beyond the Jordan, and you shall give three cities in the land of Canaan. They shall be\ncities of refuge. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NUM 35:15"}, "For the children of Israel, and for the stranger and for the foreigner living amongst them, shall these six cities be for\nrefuge, that everyone who kills any person unwittingly may flee there.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NUM 35:16"}, "\u201c\u2018But if he struck him with an instrument of iron, so that he died, he is a murderer. The murderer shall surely be put to\ndeath. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NUM 35:17"}, "If he struck him with a stone in the hand, by which a man may die, and he died, he is a murderer. The murderer shall\nsurely be put to death. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NUM 35:18"}, "Or if he struck him with a weapon of wood in the hand, by which a man may die, and he died, he is a murderer. The\nmurderer shall surely be put to death. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NUM 35:19"}, "The avenger of blood shall himself put the murderer to death. When he meets him, he shall put him to death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "NUM 35:20"}, "If he shoved him out of hatred, or hurled something at him while lying in wait, so that he died,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "NUM 35:21"}, "or in hostility struck him with his hand, so that he died, he who struck him shall surely be put to death. He is a\nmurderer. The avenger of blood shall put the murderer to death when he meets him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "NUM 35:22"}, "\u201c\u2018But if he shoved him suddenly without hostility, or hurled on him anything without lying in wait,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "NUM 35:23"}, "or with any stone, by which a man may die, not seeing him, and cast it on him so that he died, and he was not his enemy\nand not seeking his harm, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "NUM 35:24"}, "then the congregation shall judge between the striker and the avenger of blood according to these ordinances.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "NUM 35:25"}, "The congregation shall deliver the man slayer out of the hand of the avenger of blood, and the congregation shall restore\nhim to his city of refuge, where he had fled. He shall dwell therein until the death of the high priest, who was anointed with\nthe holy oil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "NUM 35:26"}, "\u201c\u2018But if the man slayer shall at any time go beyond the border of his city of refuge where he flees,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "NUM 35:27"}, "and the avenger of blood finds him outside of the border of his city of refuge, and the avenger of blood kills the man\nslayer, he shall not be guilty of blood, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "NUM 35:28"}, "because he should have remained in his city of refuge until the death of the high priest. But after the death of the high\npriest, the man slayer shall return into the land of his possession.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "NUM 35:29"}, "\u201c\u2018These things shall be for a statute and ordinance to you throughout your generations in all your dwellings.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "NUM 35:30"}, "\u201c\u2018Whoever kills any person, the murderer shall be slain based on the testimony of witnesses; but one witness shall not\ntestify alone against any person so that he dies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "NUM 35:31"}, "\u201c\u2018Moreover you shall take no ransom for the life of a murderer who is guilty of death. He shall surely be put to death.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "NUM 35:32"}, "\u201c\u2018You shall take no ransom for him who has fled to his city of refuge, that he may come again to dwell in the land before\nthe death of the priest. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "NUM 35:33"}, "\u201c\u2018So you shall not pollute the land where you live; for blood pollutes the land. No atonement can be made for the land,\nfor the blood that is shed in it, but by the blood of him who shed it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "NUM 35:34"}, "You shall not defile the land which you inhabit, where I dwell; for I, the LORD, dwell amongst the children of Israel.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "36", "sid": "NUM 36"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NUM 36:1"}, "The heads of the fathers\u2019 households of the family of the children of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of\nthe families of the sons of Yusuf, came near, and spoke before Musa and before the princes, the heads of the fathers\u2019\nhouseholds of the children of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NUM 36:2"}, "They said, \u201cThe LORD commanded my lord to give the land for inheritance by lot to the children of Israel. My lord was\ncommanded by the LORD to give the inheritance of Zelophehad our brother to his daughters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NUM 36:3"}, "If they are married to any of the sons of the other tribes of the children of Israel, then their inheritance will be taken\naway from the inheritance of our fathers, and will be added to the inheritance of the tribe to which they shall belong. So it\nwill be taken away from the lot of our inheritance. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NUM 36:4"}, "When the jubilee of the children of Israel comes, then their inheritance will be added to the inheritance of the tribe to\nwhich they shall belong. So their inheritance will be taken away from the inheritance of the tribe of our fathers.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NUM 36:5"}, "Musa commanded the children of Israel according to the LORD\u2019s word, saying, \u201cThe tribe of the sons of Yusuf speak what is\nright. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NUM 36:6"}, "This is the thing which the LORD commands concerning the daughters of Zelophehad, saying, \u2018Let them be married to whom\nthey think best, only they shall marry into the family of the tribe of their father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NUM 36:7"}, "So shall no inheritance of the children of Israel move from tribe to tribe; for the children of Israel shall all keep the\ninheritance of the tribe of his fathers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NUM 36:8"}, "Every daughter who possesses an inheritance in any tribe of the children of Israel shall be wife to one of the family of\nthe tribe of her father, that the children of Israel may each possess the inheritance of his fathers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NUM 36:9"}, "So shall no inheritance move from one tribe to another tribe; for the tribes of the children of Israel shall each keep his\nown inheritance.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NUM 36:10"}, "The daughters of Zelophehad did as the LORD commanded Musa:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NUM 36:11"}, "for Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Nuh, the daughters of Zelophehad, were married to their father\u2019s brothers\u2019 sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NUM 36:12"}, "They were married into the families of the sons of Manasseh the son of Yusuf. Their inheritance remained in the tribe of\nthe family of their father. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NUM 36:13"}, "These are the commandments and the ordinances which the LORD commanded by Musa to the children of Israel in the plains of\nMoab by the Jordan at Jericho. "]}]}